1
00:00:00,583 --> 00:00:02,293
- Where should I look?
- Towards me.

2
00:00:02,377 --> 00:00:04,170
Introduce yourself to the camera.

3
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:07,882
Hi! I'm BINI Jhoanna.

4
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:10,802
The most beautif-- Just kidding!

5
00:00:10,885 --> 00:00:12,846
I'm BINI Jhoanna.

6
00:00:12,929 --> 00:00:15,682
Hi! I'm Gwen, BINI Gwen. [chuckles]

7
00:00:15,765 --> 00:00:19,185
Hi, camera! I'm BINI Colet. [chuckles]

8
00:00:19,269 --> 00:00:21,771
Hi, everyone! I'm Mikha from BINI.

9
00:00:21,855 --> 00:00:23,690
[chuckles]

10
00:00:23,773 --> 00:00:26,276
Hi! I'm BINI Sheena.

11
00:00:26,359 --> 00:00:29,195
Hi, Blooms and everyone in the world.

12
00:00:29,279 --> 00:00:31,614
I'm Maloi from BINI!

13
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:32,741
Hi, I'm Stacey!

14
00:00:32,824 --> 00:00:36,036
I'm 21 and I'm a member of BINI.

15
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:37,078
Hi, everyone!

16
00:00:37,162 --> 00:00:41,374
I'm Maraiah Queen Arceta,
23, from Cebu! [giggles]

17
00:00:41,458 --> 00:00:48,089
[thrilling music playing]

18
00:01:05,482 --> 00:01:07,567
[Jhoanna] When I was a kid,
I think I wanted

19
00:01:07,650 --> 00:01:09,402
to be an actress more than a performer.

20
00:01:09,486 --> 00:01:12,280
I'd picture myself on a variety show

21
00:01:12,363 --> 00:01:15,200
and I'd get curious
about the singers there.

22
00:01:15,283 --> 00:01:16,785
So I would imitate them.

23
00:01:16,868 --> 00:01:19,245
I think everyone dreams
of becoming a star.

24
00:01:19,329 --> 00:01:22,082
[Sheena] Eventually, because
I was always watching TV,

25
00:01:22,165 --> 00:01:24,167
and my mom being a K-pop fan,

26
00:01:24,250 --> 00:01:26,669
I got into singing and dancing.

27
00:01:26,753 --> 00:01:28,922
Actually, when I was little,
it was all about dancing for me.

28
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:31,007
My dream was to perform on a variety show.

29
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:33,802
[Colet] Whenever I was home alone,

30
00:01:33,885 --> 00:01:35,303
I'd put on a show.

31
00:01:35,386 --> 00:01:37,597
I'd dance and sing.

32
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:39,724
I was just being cute.

33
00:01:39,808 --> 00:01:42,685
I guess I got that from
watching too much TV.

34
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:45,688
[Gwen] My mom also loves to sing.

35
00:01:45,772 --> 00:01:47,565
So, I guess she always hoped
I'd become a singer.

36
00:01:47,649 --> 00:01:49,692
I mean, even as a baby,

37
00:01:49,776 --> 00:01:54,739
I was already singing
well before I could talk.

38
00:01:54,823 --> 00:01:57,992
[Maloi] I was already belting
out tunes at 3 years old.

39
00:01:58,076 --> 00:02:00,495
Nursery rhymes were my jam.

40
00:02:00,578 --> 00:02:04,290
My parents signed me up for a dance group

41
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:06,376
that did everything
from hip-hop to ballroom.

42
00:02:06,459 --> 00:02:09,003
That's where I learned to really dance.

43
00:02:09,087 --> 00:02:10,463
[Aiah] During karaoke nights,

44
00:02:10,547 --> 00:02:12,632
I was always the one hyping everyone up

45
00:02:12,715 --> 00:02:15,176
and picking out songs
from the karaoke book.

46
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:16,761
"I'll pay for everything,
just don't make me sing!"

47
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:18,763
That's what I'd always say.

48
00:02:18,847 --> 00:02:20,223
But secretly,

49
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:22,392
like when I'm alone in my room,

50
00:02:22,475 --> 00:02:24,602
I'd record myself singing.

51
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:27,605
And then I'd listen back to it
and think, "What is this?"

52
00:02:27,689 --> 00:02:29,983
[Mikha] I was dancing
with my childhood friend.

53
00:02:30,066 --> 00:02:31,776
I was wearing pink all over.

54
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,570
It was just for fun,

55
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:35,363
not really anything serious.

56
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:39,075
But I've always enjoyed being
on stage or something like that.

57
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:41,995
[Stacey] When I was a kid,
I dreamed of becoming

58
00:02:42,078 --> 00:02:45,790
a famous actress,
like the ones I'd see on TV.

59
00:02:45,874 --> 00:02:47,667
I also dreamed of becoming Miss Universe,

60
00:02:47,750 --> 00:02:50,962
a beauty queen, a model,
even a flight attendant.

61
00:02:51,045 --> 00:02:53,006
I had a ton of dreams!

62
00:02:53,089 --> 00:02:54,799
But there's one thing
I never really aspired to,

63
00:02:54,883 --> 00:02:56,718
and that's being a famous idol.

64
00:03:12,609 --> 00:03:14,193
<i>We are the BINI!</i>

65
00:03:14,277 --> 00:03:16,362
[screaming, squealing]

66
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:23,244
[thrilling music playing]

67
00:03:26,205 --> 00:03:27,665
Eyyy!

68
00:03:29,459 --> 00:03:31,502
[elevator bell dings]

69
00:03:31,586 --> 00:03:33,129
[Jhoanna] Are your nails pretty?

70
00:03:33,671 --> 00:03:35,131
[Sheena gasps] Can I see?

71
00:03:35,215 --> 00:03:37,425
Oh, it's green. It's blue.

72
00:03:37,508 --> 00:03:39,802
- You grew your nails too long.
- [Mikha] That's just how it is.

73
00:03:39,886 --> 00:03:41,804
[Stacey] It goes with
the shape of her hand.

74
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:43,848
Do you see room 10?

75
00:03:44,724 --> 00:03:47,894
Stacey is my roommate because
they're assigning it by age.

76
00:03:49,270 --> 00:03:50,438
- I hate it.
- Yeah.

77
00:03:52,857 --> 00:03:54,359
- Wow.
- Wow!

78
00:03:55,276 --> 00:03:56,486
[exclaims, laughs]

79
00:03:56,569 --> 00:03:58,446
Oh! Wait, the mic! [giggling]

80
00:03:59,948 --> 00:04:01,366
[Colet] Oh.

81
00:04:01,449 --> 00:04:03,243
This is amazing.

82
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:04,202
[Aiah] I think this is the first time

83
00:04:04,285 --> 00:04:05,620
I got treated to a surprise like this.

84
00:04:05,703 --> 00:04:09,249
- I know, right?
- It's never happened before.

85
00:04:09,332 --> 00:04:11,167
As soon as we went in,

86
00:04:11,751 --> 00:04:13,670
we started talking about the old times.

87
00:04:13,753 --> 00:04:15,296
When we were just starting out,

88
00:04:15,380 --> 00:04:18,383
a big room like this was enough
for three or four people.

89
00:04:18,466 --> 00:04:19,968
We had to make do back then.

90
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:23,096
There were four of us in a room,
but we only had two single beds.

91
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:26,057
So, we just pushed them together

92
00:04:26,474 --> 00:04:29,352
so all of us could sleep on the bed.

93
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,772
It was super cramped. Our things
were all over the place.

94
00:04:32,855 --> 00:04:34,899
But then we started making money.

95
00:04:34,983 --> 00:04:36,693
We were able to send each other to school.

96
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:38,278
We came back from working abroad.

97
00:04:38,361 --> 00:04:40,113
We're finally able to
afford this. Just kidding.

98
00:04:41,406 --> 00:04:44,284
Wow! I can get used to this! [laughs]

99
00:04:45,285 --> 00:04:46,703
It's a special occasion.

100
00:04:46,786 --> 00:04:48,955
Only because it's our concert. [laughs]

101
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:53,793
I'm really shy.

102
00:04:53,876 --> 00:04:55,795
But preparing for this concert,

103
00:04:55,878 --> 00:04:57,797
I didn't care anymore
if I was being too loud

104
00:04:57,880 --> 00:04:59,173
and my neighbors could hear me.

105
00:04:59,257 --> 00:05:01,384
Really? I can't rehearse inside my condo.

106
00:05:01,467 --> 00:05:04,095
I was like, "Screw it!"
I had no care in the world.

107
00:05:04,178 --> 00:05:05,471
I do feel guilty about it,

108
00:05:05,555 --> 00:05:07,473
but shucks, I really need to practice.

109
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:10,435
Guys, we're on the 20th floor.

110
00:05:10,518 --> 00:05:12,937
[Sheena mimicking Jhoanna] Guys...

111
00:05:16,774 --> 00:05:18,192
The camera is too close! [laughs]

112
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:20,403
Guys, Jhoanna keeps
posting thirst traps. I give up.

113
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:23,072
- Yeah.
- Mikha uploads thirst traps too!

114
00:05:23,156 --> 00:05:25,491
- There she goes again!
- No, my TikTok's been acting up.

115
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,329
I'm freaking out!

116
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:31,080
[upbeat music playing]

117
00:05:31,164 --> 00:05:34,375
"I" is for "I love you, BINI!"

118
00:05:34,459 --> 00:05:37,045
[fans cheering]

119
00:05:38,046 --> 00:05:39,422
Eyy, eyy, eyy, eyy!

120
00:05:39,505 --> 00:05:42,300
[reporter] <i>BINI's first-ever
three-day solo concert</i>

121
00:05:42,383 --> 00:05:44,052
<i>kicks off tonight.</i>

122
00:05:44,135 --> 00:05:45,887
- Best leader!
- It's Aiah for me!

123
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:49,223
- Why Aiah?
- Mama Mary, slay-men!

124
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:50,892
[fans cheering]

125
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:52,435
I love Colet so much!

126
00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:56,272
[reporter] <i>Tonight is the night.</i>

127
00:05:56,355 --> 00:05:58,524
<i>The much-awaited first solo concert</i>

128
00:05:58,608 --> 00:06:00,568
<i>of the Nation's Girl Group, BINI...</i>

129
00:06:00,651 --> 00:06:04,072
Why Maloi? 'Cause she's
a pro at fan service.

130
00:06:04,155 --> 00:06:05,281
[reporter] Why is Gwen your bias?

131
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:07,742
She's oozing with charisma. Hits the spot!

132
00:06:07,825 --> 00:06:09,118
Love you, Mikha!

133
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:14,874
[fans chanting] BINI! BINI! BINI! BINI!

134
00:06:14,957 --> 00:06:16,459
You can do it!

135
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:20,296
You were born to do this!

136
00:06:21,547 --> 00:06:24,383
- Let's go, BINI!
- Go, girls! This is it!

137
00:06:24,467 --> 00:06:26,552
[cheering]

138
00:06:30,848 --> 00:06:32,058
Aiah!

139
00:06:32,767 --> 00:06:33,893
Go, Aiah!

140
00:06:33,976 --> 00:06:38,564
[fans cheering]

141
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:40,358
Good luck, girls!

142
00:06:40,775 --> 00:06:41,901
Good luck, girls!

143
00:06:41,984 --> 00:06:45,780
- [fans cheering]
- [music fades]

144
00:06:48,491 --> 00:06:52,036
- <i>♪ Na na na na ♪</i>
- [fans screaming]

145
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,246
<i>♪ Na na na na ♪</i>

146
00:06:55,456 --> 00:06:57,041
[dance coach] One, two, three, four.

147
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:59,794
In one, two, three, four.
To the side, girls.

148
00:06:59,877 --> 00:07:01,963
So, it's on this side.

149
00:07:04,257 --> 00:07:06,801
[Maloi] This concert
really is a dream come true.

150
00:07:06,884 --> 00:07:10,471
This is what we've been
working towards all this time.

151
00:07:10,555 --> 00:07:12,432
It's finally here.

152
00:07:12,515 --> 00:07:15,268
This is the culmination
of all the hard work.

153
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:16,519
You'll get to see it.

154
00:07:16,602 --> 00:07:18,187
Mic check.

155
00:07:18,271 --> 00:07:21,691
How do we put a new spin

156
00:07:21,774 --> 00:07:23,776
on song numbers we've already done before?

157
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,194
That's the hard part.

158
00:07:25,278 --> 00:07:28,990
How do we give it
a fresh flavor so it feels new?

159
00:07:29,073 --> 00:07:31,367
We've performed these songs
so many times before.

160
00:07:31,451 --> 00:07:34,370
["Lagi" playing]

161
00:07:38,791 --> 00:07:40,668
[soft music playing]

162
00:07:40,751 --> 00:07:43,588
[Stacey] To be honest,
I'm feeling the pressure.

163
00:07:43,671 --> 00:07:46,466
There's only nine days
to go before our concert.

164
00:07:46,549 --> 00:07:49,051
I can't help but overthink.

165
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:51,596
We really need to push ourselves

166
00:07:51,679 --> 00:07:53,890
and show everyone what we're made of.

167
00:07:56,267 --> 00:08:00,897
We record our rehearsals every day
so we can keep track of the changes.

168
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:02,064
[dance coach] Close.

169
00:08:04,275 --> 00:08:07,653
- Close.
- One, two, three four.

170
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:12,366
We're putting in long hours,
from 9am to 10pm.

171
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:14,911
That's why we record videos
of ourselves every session

172
00:08:14,994 --> 00:08:17,288
so we can review it later.

173
00:08:17,371 --> 00:08:19,582
We see a lot of progress each day

174
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:23,085
because we learn so many new things.

175
00:08:23,169 --> 00:08:25,379
We're never stuck on one thing.

176
00:08:25,463 --> 00:08:26,297
Seven, eight...

177
00:08:26,380 --> 00:08:28,841
["Lagi" concert version playing]

178
00:08:33,095 --> 00:08:34,180
Nice! Nice!

179
00:08:34,263 --> 00:08:35,431
Yes.

180
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:38,226
Still so many things to do!

181
00:08:41,020 --> 00:08:44,023
[dance coach]
And 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.

182
00:08:44,106 --> 00:08:49,487
[upbeat music playing]

183
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:54,867
[Jhoanna] I'm super happy
because the dancers we got,

184
00:08:54,951 --> 00:08:57,078
we call them our "besties."

185
00:08:57,161 --> 00:08:59,789
We treat them like
they are part of the group.

186
00:08:59,872 --> 00:09:02,458
We have so much fun
bonding and hanging out.

187
00:09:03,251 --> 00:09:04,335
[chuckles]

188
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:06,671
[groans]

189
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:11,676
It's not even a "want" anymore,
it's something we need to do.

190
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:14,303
At the end of the day,
it's for the Blooms.

191
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:16,973
And, of course, our parents
are coming to see us

192
00:09:17,056 --> 00:09:18,766
perform for the first time!

193
00:09:18,849 --> 00:09:20,268
My parents,

194
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:24,397
my entire family is flying in
to watch our first solo concert.

195
00:09:24,480 --> 00:09:25,523
So, yeah.

196
00:09:27,608 --> 00:09:30,861
[Reden] The first few
rehearsals were crazy.

197
00:09:30,945 --> 00:09:34,365
Between the production numbers
and solo performances,

198
00:09:34,448 --> 00:09:37,076
we felt overwhelmed with
all the things we needed to do.

199
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:38,953
We'd work late into the night

200
00:09:39,870 --> 00:09:41,497
to wrap up the production number.

201
00:09:41,581 --> 00:09:46,586
- [tense music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

202
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:50,464
My top priority was always making sure
the girls felt relaxed

203
00:09:50,548 --> 00:09:54,343
when we run the whole show.

204
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:59,599
But I feel we were really short on time,
on our preparations.

205
00:09:59,682 --> 00:10:02,435
I'm having a hard time picturing
the entire show in my head.

206
00:10:02,518 --> 00:10:04,186
It still feels impossible to me.

207
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:07,064
We're here, we're here,
we're here, we're here!

208
00:10:08,858 --> 00:10:10,443
Hello!

209
00:10:10,860 --> 00:10:12,069
You're early!

210
00:10:12,153 --> 00:10:15,698
[Mikha] It's our first-ever solo concert

211
00:10:15,781 --> 00:10:17,366
with a big crowd.

212
00:10:18,367 --> 00:10:19,201
And...

213
00:10:20,494 --> 00:10:24,373
Obviously, with higher numbers
come higher expectations.

214
00:10:25,750 --> 00:10:27,543
So, it's really nerve-wracking.
[chuckles softly]

215
00:10:32,214 --> 00:10:33,174
Oh, wow!

216
00:10:33,257 --> 00:10:35,468
- It's Staku.
- Oh!

217
00:10:38,054 --> 00:10:40,181
The LED screen is massive!

218
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:42,767
[Colet] Okay, here we are.

219
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:44,977
This is our first-ever concert.

220
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:46,479
We've been through so much.

221
00:10:46,562 --> 00:10:48,064
That kind of talk.

222
00:10:49,774 --> 00:10:53,944
[Stacey] Stop! Stop showing that!

223
00:10:54,862 --> 00:10:56,530
[Sheena] I'm going to cry.

224
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:02,036
- Oh!
- We looked different back then.

225
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:05,081
"Good job, girls!" Back then,
saying that felt cheesy.

226
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:06,999
We couldn't say stuff
like that to each other.

227
00:11:07,083 --> 00:11:10,670
And it felt awkward because we
weren't really close. [chuckles]

228
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:12,797
[Jhoanna] People think
everything was handed to us

229
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,424
on a silver platter. That's not true.

230
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:18,302
If they only knew how hard
we had to work to get here.

231
00:11:28,270 --> 00:11:29,397
[staff] <i>Action.</i>

232
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:32,983
<i>I'm Jhoanna Christine B. Robles,
14 years old.</i>

233
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:35,403
<i>I live in Calamba City, Laguna.</i>

234
00:11:35,486 --> 00:11:37,780
<i>Hi, I'm Maria Nicolette Vergara,</i>

235
00:11:37,863 --> 00:11:40,741
<i>16 years old, from Tagbilaran City.</i>

236
00:11:44,203 --> 00:11:46,080
<i>My name is Mikhaela Janna J. Lim,</i>

237
00:11:46,163 --> 00:11:48,582
<i>but you can call me Mikha.
I'm 14 years old.</i>

238
00:11:48,666 --> 00:11:52,253
<i>I study in San Pedro, Poveda.</i>

239
00:11:52,336 --> 00:11:53,963
<i>I'm Sheena Mae Catacutan.</i>

240
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:55,798
<i>I'm 14 years old.</i>

241
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:59,468
<i>I live at Victory Square,
Santiago City, Isabela.</i>

242
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:02,221
<i>I study at University of La Salette.</i>

243
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:03,472
<i>Good noon, everyone,</i>

244
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,975
<i>my name is Mary Loi Ricalde,</i>

245
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:07,893
<i>I'm 16 years of age,</i>

246
00:12:07,977 --> 00:12:11,564
<i>and I live in General Trias, Cavite.</i>

247
00:12:11,647 --> 00:12:14,316
[Ukulele strumming]

248
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,569
[staff] <i>Be as natural as possible.</i>

249
00:12:16,652 --> 00:12:17,945
<i>Okay, ready?</i>

250
00:12:21,782 --> 00:12:25,077
[pensive music playing]

251
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:27,746
[Lauren] The vision started before 2019.

252
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:28,831
At the time,

253
00:12:28,914 --> 00:12:31,834
ABS-CBN's plan was really
to go international already.

254
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:35,880
We wanted to create a group
that would follow in the footsteps

255
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:39,758
of successful Asian acts
like BTS and Blackpink.

256
00:12:39,842 --> 00:12:41,427
We were looking for members

257
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:44,180
who would undergo rigorous
training, be disciplined,

258
00:12:44,263 --> 00:12:49,643
and be ready to take on
the international stage.

259
00:12:49,727 --> 00:12:52,688
[tv announcer] <i>Get ready
to audition in Star Hunt!</i>

260
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:56,775
[Lauren] Star Hunt was
basically an audition caravan

261
00:12:56,859 --> 00:12:59,778
that traveled all over the Philippines

262
00:12:59,862 --> 00:13:02,114
and even to other countries.

263
00:13:02,198 --> 00:13:04,366
The goal was to find new talents

264
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:09,872
for reality and variety shows
like <i>It's Showtime,</i>

265
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:13,167
<i>The Voice, Pilipinas Got Talent,</i>

266
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,919
and <i>Pinoy Big Brother.</i>

267
00:13:17,046 --> 00:13:19,673
[MQ] That's how BINI got started.

268
00:13:19,757 --> 00:13:22,968
Director Lauren had a secret project

269
00:13:23,052 --> 00:13:27,848
and he was selecting potential members
from the <i>Star Hunt</i> auditions.

270
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:30,184
It was code-named Project Kayumanggi.

271
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:33,938
So, we wanted a Filipina, Filipino group,

272
00:13:34,021 --> 00:13:37,066
that would showcase local talent
in singing and dancing.

273
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:39,401
I've always believed, even at that time,

274
00:13:39,485 --> 00:13:41,195
we told the management,
our advantage is that

275
00:13:41,278 --> 00:13:43,822
Filipinos are naturally talented
singers and dancers.

276
00:13:43,906 --> 00:13:45,950
We need representation on the world stage.

277
00:13:46,033 --> 00:13:48,369
- [tape reeling]
- [pensive music continues]

278
00:13:48,452 --> 00:13:51,956
[Stacey] My mom and I saw
the poster for <i>Star Hunt.</i>

279
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:54,291
She was the one who encouraged me.

280
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:57,253
She asked, "Want to audition
for <i>Star Hunt</i> at Araneta?"

281
00:13:57,336 --> 00:13:58,587
[Jhoanna] They wouldn't let me audition.

282
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:00,798
They didn't want it to get
in the way of school.

283
00:14:00,881 --> 00:14:05,636
But then I got this art card
about the <i>Star Hunt</i> audition,

284
00:14:05,719 --> 00:14:07,972
and I was unusually upset
that they wouldn't let me go.

285
00:14:08,055 --> 00:14:10,224
To the point that I was crying
on our terrace.

286
00:14:10,307 --> 00:14:14,436
I had this strong feeling,
like I had to do this.

287
00:14:14,520 --> 00:14:16,939
I had no plans of auditioning.

288
00:14:17,022 --> 00:14:19,567
I was part of a dance group.
There were only two girls.

289
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:22,611
The other girl went to audition
for <i>Pinoy Big Brother.</i>

290
00:14:22,695 --> 00:14:25,364
During the interview, she
mentioned our dance group,

291
00:14:25,447 --> 00:14:28,284
so <i>Star Hunt</i> asked us to come in.

292
00:14:28,367 --> 00:14:29,493
From the top, um...

293
00:14:29,577 --> 00:14:32,997
My friend messaged me about the audition.

294
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:34,790
I printed all the documents

295
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:37,751
and had my mom sign because
I was only 14 years old.

296
00:14:37,835 --> 00:14:41,088
I was already a long-time
avid fan of <i>Pinoy Big Brother.</i>

297
00:14:41,171 --> 00:14:44,884
I really didn't have the guts
to audition though.

298
00:14:44,967 --> 00:14:48,304
Like, who am I?
I don't sing, I don't dance.

299
00:14:48,387 --> 00:14:50,180
Not until I joined the Grand Audition.

300
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:52,892
[Maloi] My sister was the one
who was auditioning.

301
00:14:52,975 --> 00:14:55,019
It was probably her third time trying out.

302
00:14:55,102 --> 00:14:57,313
I went along to support her.

303
00:14:57,396 --> 00:14:58,981
Then my mom pushed me to audition too.

304
00:14:59,064 --> 00:15:01,066
And I said, "I don't want to."

305
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:03,277
She told me, "Come on.
What have you got to lose?

306
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:04,862
You just have to stand in line."

307
00:15:04,945 --> 00:15:07,239
They were holding auditions in Bohol.

308
00:15:07,323 --> 00:15:08,282
I was super shy.

309
00:15:08,365 --> 00:15:09,992
I'd never auditioned
for anything like that before.

310
00:15:10,075 --> 00:15:13,329
But at that time, I really wanted to.

311
00:15:13,412 --> 00:15:16,999
I just woke up my mom and
asked to drive me to the mall.

312
00:15:17,082 --> 00:15:19,501
I auditioned in a different province
since there wasn't one in my hometown.

313
00:15:19,585 --> 00:15:21,503
So, I had to travel a long distance.

314
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:24,965
I had to travel by land
for 8 hours just to try out.

315
00:15:25,049 --> 00:15:26,091
There were so many people.

316
00:15:26,175 --> 00:15:27,509
[Jhoanna] When we got there at 6am,

317
00:15:27,593 --> 00:15:29,511
I was confident I'd be first in line.

318
00:15:29,595 --> 00:15:31,680
But the line was already super long.

319
00:15:31,764 --> 00:15:33,891
We queued the whole day
because you can't leave

320
00:15:33,974 --> 00:15:35,768
once you're inside Araneta.

321
00:15:35,851 --> 00:15:36,977
I didn't have anything on me.

322
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:39,521
Not even a bottle of water. Nothing.

323
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:40,773
I was stuck there from the afternoon

324
00:15:40,856 --> 00:15:41,899
until two in the morning.

325
00:15:41,982 --> 00:15:43,150
I didn't have enough money.

326
00:15:43,233 --> 00:15:44,360
I was starving.

327
00:15:44,443 --> 00:15:47,863
I couldn't even get a drink
as we couldn't leave the queue.

328
00:15:47,947 --> 00:15:49,281
I was on my own.

329
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:51,492
So, I didn't get to eat.

330
00:15:51,575 --> 00:15:53,786
I was about to quit the audition
just to get something to eat.

331
00:15:53,869 --> 00:15:56,288
But then I heard a voice in my head,

332
00:15:56,372 --> 00:15:59,792
maybe it was God or an angel,
saying, "Keep going."

333
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:01,168
I was freaking out because
so many people were watching.

334
00:16:01,251 --> 00:16:02,503
Then they suddenly asked me to sing.

335
00:16:02,586 --> 00:16:03,837
Next thing I know,

336
00:16:03,921 --> 00:16:05,839
they were telling me to audition
for <i>Pinoy Big Brother.</i>

337
00:16:06,382 --> 00:16:09,385
What was I supposed to do?
They made the decision for me.

338
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:11,595
So I auditioned for <i>Pinoy Big Brother.</i>

339
00:16:11,679 --> 00:16:13,305
[bright music playing]

340
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:17,142
<i>I'm Sheena,
the Dancing Princess of Isabela.</i>

341
00:16:20,771 --> 00:16:25,484
<i>I'm Gwen, the Beautiful Sweetie of Albay.</i>

342
00:16:25,567 --> 00:16:27,903
So yeah, I got into <i>Pinoy Big Brother</i>

343
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:29,405
and became a housemate.

344
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:32,700
[Aiah] It didn't work out.

345
00:16:32,783 --> 00:16:35,285
It took me like several months
to get over it

346
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:37,788
and accept that it just wasn't for me.

347
00:16:38,747 --> 00:16:40,624
[Jhoanna] So, I was given a star.

348
00:16:40,708 --> 00:16:42,292
Then we had to stay until midnight.

349
00:16:42,376 --> 00:16:44,628
I thought that was it.
I was going to be a star.

350
00:16:44,712 --> 00:16:46,588
But nope, there were so many callbacks.

351
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:50,092
[staff] Smile, show your teeth.

352
00:16:50,175 --> 00:16:51,468
[Colet] We didn't know it was for P-pop.

353
00:16:51,552 --> 00:16:53,470
They just made us dance and sing.

354
00:16:53,554 --> 00:16:55,889
I remember telling my sister,
"What's all this for?"

355
00:16:55,973 --> 00:16:58,475
It was scary because they kept
making us dance and sing.

356
00:16:58,559 --> 00:17:01,270
Who knows where they'll take us?
Just kidding.

357
00:17:01,353 --> 00:17:02,479
I think it was the third callback

358
00:17:02,563 --> 00:17:05,190
before the five-day elimination
at the bootcamp.

359
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:08,694
It's quite rare to find people
who can sing and dance.

360
00:17:08,777 --> 00:17:11,363
So it was quite tough to look
for people who could do both.

361
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:12,781
We found some.

362
00:17:12,865 --> 00:17:14,491
Then we held a bootcamp

363
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:17,870
to further trim them down.

364
00:17:17,953 --> 00:17:22,499
[lively music playing]

365
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,877
[Colet] There were like 200 of us,

366
00:17:24,960 --> 00:17:27,087
a mix of guys and girls.

367
00:17:27,171 --> 00:17:29,339
In those five days,

368
00:17:30,049 --> 00:17:31,300
they were cutting people.

369
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:36,597
[lively music continues]

370
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:39,183
That's when I saw Stacey
for the first time.

371
00:17:39,266 --> 00:17:40,893
She was wearing pink from head-to-toe.

372
00:17:40,976 --> 00:17:43,520
[Maloi] She wore pink shorts,
pink top, and pink heels.

373
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:45,230
We were going to dance!

374
00:17:45,314 --> 00:17:47,399
I was like, "Why is she
wearing heels to an audition?"

375
00:17:47,483 --> 00:17:48,692
It was so weird.

376
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:50,611
[laughs]

377
00:17:50,694 --> 00:17:52,362
<i>What's your description of me?</i>

378
00:17:52,446 --> 00:17:54,615
[Stacey] My first impression of Jhoanna?

379
00:17:54,698 --> 00:17:56,033
A clout chaser! I'm joking.

380
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:58,410
This kid is so hyper.
She has so much energy.

381
00:17:58,494 --> 00:17:59,870
She'd always carry a camera
around and say, "Hello!"

382
00:17:59,953 --> 00:18:01,622
That's how she was!

383
00:18:01,705 --> 00:18:04,374
I thought Colet was, like,
only 14 years old at that time.

384
00:18:04,458 --> 00:18:07,711
Now, she's the complete opposite
of how she was before.

385
00:18:07,795 --> 00:18:10,172
Back then, she was so quiet.
She hardly spoke.

386
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:13,759
In Bohol, Tagalog feels like
a foreign language to us.

387
00:18:13,842 --> 00:18:16,261
So to be safe, I just didn't talk.

388
00:18:16,345 --> 00:18:18,138
<i>Look, look. Look at my ankles.
They're gonna stay in the same place</i>

389
00:18:18,222 --> 00:18:19,973
<i>but they're gonna open up like that.</i>

390
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:21,767
[Stacey] Mikha sounded so posh before.

391
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:24,728
She'd always speak in English
so it was hard talking to her.

392
00:18:24,812 --> 00:18:26,855
Girl, I won't waste my time talking to you

393
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,982
if you'll just give me a hard time!

394
00:18:29,066 --> 00:18:30,609
[staff] <i>How was your performance?</i>

395
00:18:30,692 --> 00:18:31,944
<i>It was fun.</i>

396
00:18:32,027 --> 00:18:34,029
[Maloi] It was like do or die.
That's how intense it was.

397
00:18:34,113 --> 00:18:37,574
One mistake and you're out of there.

398
00:18:37,658 --> 00:18:39,284
<i>Colet, let's practice over there.</i>

399
00:18:39,368 --> 00:18:43,622
- [indistinct chatter]
- [girls vocalizing]

400
00:18:44,373 --> 00:18:45,666
[Mikha] I mean, I'm pretty competitive.

401
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:48,794
But on the third day,
I called my mom, crying.

402
00:18:48,877 --> 00:18:50,879
I was like, "I can't do this anymore."

403
00:18:50,963 --> 00:18:52,422
I remember asking Maloi, "Do you
think they've already picked?"

404
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:55,008
We had those moments.

405
00:18:55,092 --> 00:18:57,761
There were folders with our names on them.

406
00:18:57,845 --> 00:19:00,180
If they call your name,
you wouldn't immediately know

407
00:19:00,264 --> 00:19:02,266
whether you've made it in or you're out.

408
00:19:02,349 --> 00:19:04,893
If I called your name,
come up to the front.

409
00:19:04,977 --> 00:19:06,770
[Stacey] I had one thing on
my mind during boot camp:

410
00:19:06,854 --> 00:19:09,314
"I will do my best,
and God will do the rest."

411
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:10,566
I already failed to make it
to <i>Pinoy Big Brother,</i>

412
00:19:10,649 --> 00:19:12,317
so I was determined to do well in this.

413
00:19:12,401 --> 00:19:16,029
I wanted to show everyone
my fighting spirit.

414
00:19:17,281 --> 00:19:18,866
[Colet] On the third day,

415
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:21,076
they made us do a killer workout.

416
00:19:21,160 --> 00:19:23,954
My god, they made us
do planks and all that.

417
00:19:24,037 --> 00:19:26,999
I had never worked out like that before.

418
00:19:27,082 --> 00:19:30,127
At that time, I thought,
"No, I can't do this."

419
00:19:30,210 --> 00:19:32,963
[coach] Guys, don't lean back!
You'll strain yourselves!

420
00:19:33,046 --> 00:19:35,716
Go! Higher!

421
00:19:37,676 --> 00:19:39,469
[Lauren] So far, out of the 50,

422
00:19:40,179 --> 00:19:42,764
we think you lot...

423
00:19:43,473 --> 00:19:46,935
have the most potential to be launched.

424
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:50,772
- [overlapping shouts, cheers]
- [upbeat music playing]

425
00:19:51,607 --> 00:19:56,069
[Colet] They put us in a house for a month
to see if we could handle it.

426
00:19:56,153 --> 00:19:57,196
I was so excited.

427
00:19:57,279 --> 00:20:01,491
For the first time, at 14,
I'm doing something like this!

428
00:20:01,575 --> 00:20:04,286
[laughs] I'm feeling shy!

429
00:20:04,369 --> 00:20:05,787
It was my dream to be
on <i>Pinoy Big Brother,</i>

430
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:08,874
so I felt like I was becoming a housemate.

431
00:20:08,957 --> 00:20:11,084
There were about 11 names
on the final list.

432
00:20:11,168 --> 00:20:14,296
And we still needed
to solidify the line-up.

433
00:20:14,379 --> 00:20:15,339
[drumming]

434
00:20:15,964 --> 00:20:20,886
[electric guitar playing]

435
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:29,186
["Karera" playing]

436
00:20:33,941 --> 00:20:36,318
<i>♪ Take it easy ♪</i>

437
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:39,780
<i>♪ Life is not a race ♪</i>

438
00:20:41,365 --> 00:20:46,078
<i>♪ Life is... Whoa oh ♪</i>

439
00:20:46,161 --> 00:20:46,995
Mic...

440
00:20:47,871 --> 00:20:49,206
Mic check.

441
00:20:49,289 --> 00:20:51,458
[MQ] When the eighth season of
<i>Pinoy Big Brother</i> wrapped up,

442
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:56,171
Sheena and Gwen were endorsed to me.

443
00:21:02,386 --> 00:21:04,096
[Sheena] During that time,
we weren't close friends yet.

444
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:06,890
Among us girls, there was
tension from the competition,

445
00:21:06,974 --> 00:21:09,977
which pushed us to put on airs
and led us to form cliques.

446
00:21:10,060 --> 00:21:12,396
So I was closer to one group
than the rest.

447
00:21:14,481 --> 00:21:17,192
[Mikha] I was like, "Oh!
New members? Okay."

448
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:19,987
I didn't know they'd be
adding more members

449
00:21:20,070 --> 00:21:21,655
who weren't there from the start.

450
00:21:22,906 --> 00:21:24,992
[Gwen] I wasn't mentally prepared.

451
00:21:25,075 --> 00:21:28,328
I just got out of the Big Brother House,

452
00:21:28,412 --> 00:21:31,123
and you're telling me I'll be
confined in another house?

453
00:21:34,084 --> 00:21:37,963
We watched them exit
the Big Brother House.

454
00:21:38,046 --> 00:21:39,172
To be honest, we were intimidated.

455
00:21:39,256 --> 00:21:41,091
They just came out of a reality show.

456
00:21:41,174 --> 00:21:43,593
They had the advantage of being popular.

457
00:21:43,677 --> 00:21:44,511
[Gwen] I call dibs on that spot.

458
00:21:44,594 --> 00:21:46,096
Hey! I already claimed that spot!

459
00:21:46,179 --> 00:21:47,889
- No, this is your spot.
- That's what I'm saying.

460
00:21:47,973 --> 00:21:50,100
I'm calling dibs on that space.
This spot is all yours.

461
00:21:50,183 --> 00:21:51,476
Oh, right.

462
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:52,811
[Stacey] Okay, we've got competition.

463
00:21:52,894 --> 00:21:53,812
I'm competing with everyone.

464
00:21:55,939 --> 00:21:57,983
[Matthew] I don't think
they had an inkling

465
00:21:58,066 --> 00:22:00,319
that we were forming
a girl group and a boy group.

466
00:22:00,402 --> 00:22:03,905
I remember when Coach Mickey asked me
who I wanted in the final line-up,

467
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:05,490
I only had three names in mind.

468
00:22:05,574 --> 00:22:06,491
[chuckling]

469
00:22:07,492 --> 00:22:08,535
[Lauren] I didn't notice her at that time.

470
00:22:08,618 --> 00:22:10,495
I think she was too timid.

471
00:22:10,579 --> 00:22:12,748
They missed Aiah in one of the auditions.

472
00:22:12,831 --> 00:22:13,790
And then, eventually,

473
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:16,626
when they were looking back
at the audition videos,

474
00:22:16,710 --> 00:22:17,961
they saw Aiah.

475
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:21,089
[Matthew] I met Aiah
in a different project.

476
00:22:21,173 --> 00:22:22,632
I think it was for another group.

477
00:22:22,716 --> 00:22:26,720
She was with more mature girls.
But I saw her potential then.

478
00:22:26,803 --> 00:22:28,388
I asked her, "How old are you?"

479
00:22:28,472 --> 00:22:29,723
I don't know. They probably thought,

480
00:22:29,806 --> 00:22:32,476
"Oh, she's too young. Let's move
her to another project."

481
00:22:32,559 --> 00:22:36,813
There's this girl from another project
who I think is perfect for this.

482
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:38,690
["I Feel Good" playing]

483
00:22:38,774 --> 00:22:41,902
<i>♪ I feel good I hope we never part ♪</i>

484
00:22:41,985 --> 00:22:46,323
<i>♪ Can't explain it
Feels like a rainbow in the sky ♪</i>

485
00:22:46,406 --> 00:22:49,993
<i>♪ Yeah, I feel good
When you're holding my hand ♪</i>

486
00:22:50,077 --> 00:22:54,998
<i>♪ I'm in paradise Oh, I'm in paradise ♪</i>

487
00:22:55,082 --> 00:22:58,418
<i>♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ♪</i>

488
00:22:58,502 --> 00:23:02,506
<i>♪ Like I'm on cloud nine
You're the dream of mine ♪</i>

489
00:23:02,589 --> 00:23:06,384
<i>♪ Ooh ooh ooh ooh ♪</i>

490
00:23:06,468 --> 00:23:10,889
<i>♪ Always on my mind
In every dream of mine ♪</i>

491
00:23:10,972 --> 00:23:14,267
Hi, everyone! I'm the new addition

492
00:23:14,351 --> 00:23:15,477
to the Star Hunt camp,

493
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:18,939
and I hope to catch up
on training quickly.

494
00:23:21,858 --> 00:23:23,401
Hello!

495
00:23:23,485 --> 00:23:25,362
- Hi!
- Good morning!

496
00:23:25,445 --> 00:23:27,989
[Aiah] Most of them went through boot camp

497
00:23:28,073 --> 00:23:29,574
and since then have been
training together.

498
00:23:29,658 --> 00:23:32,285
And then, I was added as the last member.

499
00:23:32,369 --> 00:23:34,788
I was so intimidated, because...

500
00:23:34,871 --> 00:23:36,915
- Hi!
- Hi!

501
00:23:36,998 --> 00:23:40,001
This is Aiah. Let's all welcome Aiah.

502
00:23:40,085 --> 00:23:42,212
We have a beauty queen here.

503
00:23:42,295 --> 00:23:44,172
Stacey's a beauty queen.

504
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:45,215
- Yeah, Stacey!
- Nice!

505
00:23:45,298 --> 00:23:47,968
Aiah is a beauty queen too.

506
00:23:48,051 --> 00:23:51,012
Yeah, I just recently won
a beauty pageant.

507
00:23:51,096 --> 00:23:52,889
Well, Stacey's the queen of makeup.

508
00:23:52,973 --> 00:23:54,808
[laughs] She's always fixing her makeup.

509
00:23:54,891 --> 00:23:58,061
During breaks, you'll always see
her in front of a mirror.

510
00:23:58,145 --> 00:23:59,896
[Aiah] They already had inside jokes.

511
00:23:59,980 --> 00:24:03,108
I'd just laugh along
even though I didn't get them.

512
00:24:03,191 --> 00:24:05,485
In the beginning, we didn't really click.

513
00:24:05,569 --> 00:24:07,195
You know, different personalities,

514
00:24:07,279 --> 00:24:09,823
different upbringings.

515
00:24:09,906 --> 00:24:13,410
When I saw Colet, I was like,
"Whoa, she's scary."

516
00:24:13,493 --> 00:24:15,537
She looked like Anger from <i>Inside Out.</i>

517
00:24:15,620 --> 00:24:19,583
[bright music playing]

518
00:24:19,666 --> 00:24:21,543
[Reden] Then, they started
training with the Koreans.

519
00:24:21,626 --> 00:24:23,003
During that time, we also wanted to see

520
00:24:23,086 --> 00:24:26,798
how they would get along
with their teammates.

521
00:24:26,882 --> 00:24:30,844
At first, there were times
when we would clash.

522
00:24:33,680 --> 00:24:35,891
[Jovy] I saw how tough it was for them

523
00:24:35,974 --> 00:24:39,311
to switch from Filipino to Korean coaches.

524
00:24:39,394 --> 00:24:41,021
They had to adjust
to a totally different system.

525
00:24:44,900 --> 00:24:47,736
- Why are you crying?
- [sniffles]

526
00:24:47,819 --> 00:24:49,613
[Korean coach]

527
00:24:51,698 --> 00:24:54,242
[Mikha] During those
Korean training sessions,

528
00:24:54,326 --> 00:24:57,287
I didn't know what to do.
I almost gave up.

529
00:24:57,370 --> 00:24:59,414
I really struggled to adjust.

530
00:25:01,458 --> 00:25:02,459
Aah!

531
00:25:05,295 --> 00:25:06,713
Hey! [cackles]

532
00:25:06,796 --> 00:25:08,715
[Sheena] But it was during
the Korean training sessions

533
00:25:08,798 --> 00:25:10,967
when we girls learned to move in sync.

534
00:25:11,551 --> 00:25:16,431
[speaking in Korean]

535
00:25:16,514 --> 00:25:17,891
Five, six, seven!

536
00:25:17,974 --> 00:25:19,726
That's nice!

537
00:25:19,809 --> 00:25:22,604
One, two, three, four!

538
00:25:24,856 --> 00:25:26,483
[Lauren] We had Korean trainers.

539
00:25:26,566 --> 00:25:27,901
They were very strict.

540
00:25:27,984 --> 00:25:29,903
Their program was very challenging.

541
00:25:29,986 --> 00:25:33,198
I will never forget how
the girls struggled

542
00:25:33,281 --> 00:25:34,908
when they were put on a diet.

543
00:25:34,991 --> 00:25:36,826
They ate so little even when
they were so exhausted.

544
00:25:36,910 --> 00:25:40,288
Food only consisted of bananas, eggs...

545
00:25:40,372 --> 00:25:41,915
That's all we had.

546
00:25:41,998 --> 00:25:42,874
Assess yourselves.

547
00:25:42,958 --> 00:25:47,587
Identify areas for improvement
and what else you can learn.

548
00:25:47,671 --> 00:25:52,300
And whatever happens, whoever gets cut...

549
00:25:53,802 --> 00:25:57,889
We will do something about your careers.

550
00:25:57,973 --> 00:25:59,432
Your journey won't end here.

551
00:25:59,516 --> 00:26:01,351
Don't give up. Don't give up, kids.

552
00:26:01,434 --> 00:26:04,020
We went through 3 evaluations
under our Korean trainers.

553
00:26:04,104 --> 00:26:05,563
Whenever we'd hear "evaluation,"

554
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:07,274
it automatically meant
someone was getting the boot.

555
00:26:07,732 --> 00:26:10,318
[Mickey] It's really sad.

556
00:26:10,402 --> 00:26:13,738
Again, I'm happy to do it with only five
or seven.

557
00:26:13,822 --> 00:26:16,616
Because I don't see it
in you guys right now.

558
00:26:16,700 --> 00:26:18,702
None of you are showing passion.

559
00:26:18,785 --> 00:26:20,787
It's like your hearts aren't in this.

560
00:26:20,870 --> 00:26:23,915
[Reden] We focused on those
who were really passionate.

561
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:26,001
It doesn't matter
if they weren't the best yet

562
00:26:26,084 --> 00:26:29,170
as long as they were eager to improve
and were giving their all.

563
00:26:29,254 --> 00:26:30,797
We were always asking,
"Do we keep them or not?"

564
00:26:30,880 --> 00:26:32,799
Of course, we'd like to think

565
00:26:32,882 --> 00:26:36,303
that each girl has
something to offer the group.

566
00:26:36,386 --> 00:26:38,263
[Matthew] Gwen pretty much
kept to herself.

567
00:26:38,346 --> 00:26:41,349
I wasn't even sure if she was
into what she was doing.

568
00:26:42,976 --> 00:26:44,769
[MQ] She was fresh out
of the Big Brother House

569
00:26:44,853 --> 00:26:47,105
when she went straight to boot camp.

570
00:26:47,188 --> 00:26:50,400
So, she got burned out and quit.

571
00:26:50,483 --> 00:26:51,609
The training was too much for me.

572
00:26:51,693 --> 00:26:54,988
And since I'm not a dancer,
I felt discouraged many times.

573
00:26:56,281 --> 00:26:57,782
[Maloi] It got us thinking
what's best for us

574
00:26:57,866 --> 00:26:59,200
and what each of us really want.

575
00:26:59,284 --> 00:27:01,911
It brought out our competitive side.

576
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:04,998
Because even though we've
made it to the boot camp,

577
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:09,961
we still had to fight for our spot.

578
00:27:10,045 --> 00:27:11,838
It didn't help that we were being ranked.

579
00:27:11,921 --> 00:27:14,299
Then, after training,
we rarely hung out together.

580
00:27:14,382 --> 00:27:16,676
We took to our own little groups.

581
00:27:16,760 --> 00:27:21,806
Passing judgment drove a wedge between us,
splitting us into little cliques.

582
00:27:21,890 --> 00:27:23,975
For me, it was just supposed
to be a stepping stone.

583
00:27:24,059 --> 00:27:26,102
Because initially, I didn't want
to be in a girl group.

584
00:27:26,186 --> 00:27:28,229
Alright, shall we move on?

585
00:27:29,064 --> 00:27:29,981
Shall we move on

586
00:27:30,065 --> 00:27:31,691
or do you want to give
this one another go?

587
00:27:31,775 --> 00:27:35,236
<i>♪ Mirror, mirror When will he notice me? ♪</i>

588
00:27:36,780 --> 00:27:38,615
[Gwen] Yes, I went home.

589
00:27:38,698 --> 00:27:41,910
I spent some time thinking,
made a few realizations,

590
00:27:41,993 --> 00:27:43,620
and I prayed.

591
00:27:43,703 --> 00:27:46,206
"Lord, if they accepted me back,
I'm never quitting again."

592
00:27:46,289 --> 00:27:48,375
Because it means it is my calling.

593
00:27:48,458 --> 00:27:49,793
Eventually, Gwen realized

594
00:27:49,876 --> 00:27:52,629
that this is really what she wanted.

595
00:27:52,712 --> 00:27:54,089
Can they really handle
something like this?

596
00:27:54,172 --> 00:27:55,673
We had to assess everything.

597
00:27:55,757 --> 00:27:57,801
They were handpicked.

598
00:27:57,884 --> 00:27:59,302
We took everything into consideration.

599
00:27:59,386 --> 00:28:02,097
Their mental health,
work ethic, attitude, skills...

600
00:28:02,180 --> 00:28:03,807
We did all the nitty-gritty.

601
00:28:03,890 --> 00:28:08,645
They had to cope with the stress
of possibly being cut.

602
00:28:08,728 --> 00:28:11,106
They weren't sure if they'd
make it to the final group.

603
00:28:11,189 --> 00:28:16,027
I'll be honest, my threshold
for a girl group

604
00:28:16,111 --> 00:28:17,821
was really only five members.

605
00:28:19,906 --> 00:28:23,284
[gloomy music playing]

606
00:28:23,368 --> 00:28:24,911
I have so much to pack.

607
00:28:24,994 --> 00:28:30,500
[sobbing]

608
00:28:30,583 --> 00:28:35,588
[gloomy music continues]

609
00:28:35,672 --> 00:28:37,382
I envy you. But you go, girl!

610
00:28:38,341 --> 00:28:39,509
[sniffles]

611
00:28:39,592 --> 00:28:41,386
We'll still see each other.

612
00:28:42,804 --> 00:28:46,850
[sobbing]

613
00:28:46,933 --> 00:28:49,394
[Lauren] Throughout the course
of the boot camp,

614
00:28:49,477 --> 00:28:50,895
we saw dynamics of the group develop.

615
00:28:50,979 --> 00:28:52,814
They didn't get along immediately.

616
00:28:52,897 --> 00:28:55,191
Eventually, we ended up with eight girls.

617
00:28:55,275 --> 00:28:57,402
We went through hell. No joke.

618
00:28:57,485 --> 00:29:00,321
It was a week of uncertainty.

619
00:29:00,405 --> 00:29:02,991
You never know when you'd get cut.

620
00:29:03,074 --> 00:29:05,785
It was our final evaluation
with our Korean trainers.

621
00:29:05,869 --> 00:29:09,372
We thought after that,
only five of us would make it.

622
00:29:09,456 --> 00:29:11,875
Actually, we were hoping
it would be down to five.

623
00:29:11,958 --> 00:29:13,918
It's a bit cruel to eliminate
only one person, right?

624
00:29:14,002 --> 00:29:15,879
So, we were like, "Just eliminate three."

625
00:29:15,962 --> 00:29:18,089
Director Lauren made the
announcement via Zoom.

626
00:29:18,173 --> 00:29:21,092
<i>I'd like you to be able
to support each other</i>

627
00:29:21,176 --> 00:29:23,386
<i>all throughout the journey.</i>

628
00:29:23,470 --> 00:29:27,390
<i>We'd also like to announce
this is already the final group.</i>

629
00:29:27,474 --> 00:29:29,142
<i>We'll launch you as a group of eight</i>

630
00:29:29,225 --> 00:29:31,686
<i>and we'll not take out
anybody from the group.</i>

631
00:29:31,770 --> 00:29:33,688
[clapping, cheering]

632
00:29:33,772 --> 00:29:36,065
<i>Congratulations to everyone.</i>

633
00:29:36,149 --> 00:29:37,567
<i>For the hard work...</i>

634
00:29:37,650 --> 00:29:39,778
[Maloi] It was such a relief, you know?

635
00:29:39,861 --> 00:29:41,696
We were so happy,
but also really grateful.

636
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:43,448
It's like you have
that feeling in your gut

637
00:29:43,782 --> 00:29:47,243
that you cannot take out
anyone from those eight.

638
00:29:47,327 --> 00:29:49,162
It felt right and I was happy

639
00:29:49,245 --> 00:29:52,540
that Director Lauren also felt that way.

640
00:29:52,624 --> 00:29:54,626
Even though things
were a bit chaotic at first,

641
00:29:54,709 --> 00:29:56,503
I guess it's fate
that there were eight of us.

642
00:29:56,586 --> 00:30:01,382
It's meant to be that we came
from different parts of the country.

643
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:06,846
Because we each bring
something unique to the table.

644
00:30:06,930 --> 00:30:09,849
They say 'B' is lucky.
You know, BTS, Blackpink.

645
00:30:09,933 --> 00:30:11,184
One day, it just came to me

646
00:30:11,267 --> 00:30:13,478
that I wanted to call them BINI.

647
00:30:13,561 --> 00:30:14,896
These eight girls...

648
00:30:14,979 --> 00:30:18,024
There's a certain magic
when they come together.

649
00:30:18,107 --> 00:30:25,031
[singing "Pantropiko"]

650
00:30:40,004 --> 00:30:46,970
[singing continues]

651
00:30:49,472 --> 00:30:51,891
- It's really different.
- The tone is different.

652
00:30:51,975 --> 00:30:54,519
[Jovy] And part of the announcement was,

653
00:30:54,602 --> 00:30:56,646
"You guys can't go home
to your families for a while."

654
00:30:56,729 --> 00:30:58,982
The biggest challenge at that time was...

655
00:31:01,484 --> 00:31:04,571
[reporter 1] <i>President Duterte
is placing the entire Luzon</i>

656
00:31:04,654 --> 00:31:07,115
<i>under Enhanced Community Quarantine.</i>

657
00:31:07,198 --> 00:31:09,367
[reporter 2] <i>The surge
in COVID-19 positive cases</i>

658
00:31:09,450 --> 00:31:11,828
<i>is a cause for concern...</i>

659
00:31:12,996 --> 00:31:15,290
[man] <i>You're watching them live, guys.</i>

660
00:31:20,670 --> 00:31:26,092
[indistinct chattering]

661
00:31:26,175 --> 00:31:29,679
[indistinct chattering]

662
00:31:38,646 --> 00:31:41,065
[Jovy] That was one of the hard
decisions we had to make.

663
00:31:41,149 --> 00:31:44,527
We were deliberating
whether to send them home

664
00:31:45,445 --> 00:31:48,197
or keep them here due to the lockdown.

665
00:31:48,281 --> 00:31:53,870
We're talking about singing and dancing.
How do you teach that online?

666
00:31:53,953 --> 00:31:55,246
We were hit with a double whammy.

667
00:31:55,330 --> 00:31:58,207
We were preparing for the possible
non-renewal of our franchise

668
00:31:58,291 --> 00:31:59,459
and we thought we can survive that.

669
00:31:59,542 --> 00:32:02,545
But we never planned
for a global pandemic.

670
00:32:02,629 --> 00:32:06,382
If we send them home,
we don't know if they'll come back,

671
00:32:06,466 --> 00:32:08,259
and if this project
will even push through.

672
00:32:08,343 --> 00:32:10,637
<i>Okay, we're about to shoot</i>

673
00:32:11,137 --> 00:32:13,139
<i>Stacey's solo performance.</i>

674
00:32:14,265 --> 00:32:16,017
[Reden] The only way to keep the training

675
00:32:16,100 --> 00:32:17,977
on track was to lock-in.

676
00:32:18,061 --> 00:32:19,395
We basically housed them in one place.

677
00:32:19,479 --> 00:32:24,859
When I talked to the girls,
they were totally on board with it.

678
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:29,781
[Sheena] Because of the pandemic,

679
00:32:29,864 --> 00:32:32,408
we were stuck inside
for like 8 or 9 months, just us.

680
00:32:34,786 --> 00:32:35,995
[Nelson] I've been with BINI

681
00:32:36,079 --> 00:32:38,915
since <i>Pinoy Big Brother</i> to the BINI House.

682
00:32:38,998 --> 00:32:43,336
Since going out was restricted
during the pandemic,

683
00:32:43,419 --> 00:32:47,423
we produced all our content
inside the BINI House.

684
00:32:54,806 --> 00:32:56,474
<i>It is Jeff's wish</i>

685
00:32:56,557 --> 00:32:58,768
<i>to have you girls
perform live in the studio.</i>

686
00:32:58,851 --> 00:33:01,854
<i>But it's not possible right now.</i>

687
00:33:01,938 --> 00:33:06,484
Creating content online is the best way
to put themselves out there.

688
00:33:06,567 --> 00:33:08,569
<i>Yes, guys. We're still here.</i>

689
00:33:09,862 --> 00:33:12,365
<i>We're carrying on with our Kumu Live.</i>

690
00:33:12,448 --> 00:33:15,702
<i>Why are you crying? Don't cry!</i>

691
00:33:15,785 --> 00:33:17,537
<i>- Don't cry.
- They're upset.</i>

692
00:33:19,163 --> 00:33:22,000
[Gwen] The pandemic was driving us crazy.

693
00:33:22,083 --> 00:33:25,294
We were getting sick of each other.

694
00:33:25,378 --> 00:33:26,462
We couldn't go anywhere.

695
00:33:26,546 --> 00:33:30,383
We couldn't even see our parents.

696
00:33:30,466 --> 00:33:34,804
I had to talk to the parents one by one
to get them to say yes to this.

697
00:33:34,887 --> 00:33:39,225
It was a leap of faith to trust
the management like that.

698
00:33:39,308 --> 00:33:42,103
[Jovy] The hardest part
was deciding to keep them.

699
00:33:42,186 --> 00:33:45,189
The uncertainty of when they'll be out
and when they'll see their families again,

700
00:33:45,273 --> 00:33:46,357
that's what's tough.

701
00:33:48,735 --> 00:33:52,238
[Maan] The big worry
is COVID-19 getting inside

702
00:33:52,321 --> 00:33:55,491
the <i>Pinoy Big Brother</i> house
and spreading to everyone.

703
00:33:55,575 --> 00:33:59,412
So, anything they ask for, like food,
gets delivered to the doorstep.

704
00:33:59,495 --> 00:34:03,541
They'd cook something
and then ask me to try it.

705
00:34:03,624 --> 00:34:05,126
It's good.

706
00:34:05,209 --> 00:34:09,964
Since there were only three guys
in the BINI House,

707
00:34:10,048 --> 00:34:12,425
we made do with what we had.

708
00:34:13,051 --> 00:34:15,511
We acted as the art department

709
00:34:15,595 --> 00:34:16,763
while shooting videos for BINI.

710
00:34:16,846 --> 00:34:19,265
[Maan] That experience
really opened my eyes

711
00:34:19,348 --> 00:34:20,767
to how amazing these kids are.

712
00:34:20,850 --> 00:34:22,185
They were always so eager to lend a hand.

713
00:34:22,268 --> 00:34:24,479
They'd be like, "Miss Maan,
let's set it up like this."

714
00:34:24,562 --> 00:34:26,564
They'd set up the camera,

715
00:34:26,647 --> 00:34:28,441
adjust the lights, the whole thing.

716
00:34:28,524 --> 00:34:31,527
At first, we were trying
to stay positive, you know?

717
00:34:31,611 --> 00:34:32,737
And the pandemic,

718
00:34:32,820 --> 00:34:35,406
it dragged on for not just months,
but years.

719
00:34:35,490 --> 00:34:37,784
<i>- Hi, everyone!
- Hi!</i>

720
00:34:37,867 --> 00:34:41,537
<i>Hi! So, we just finished recording.</i>

721
00:34:41,621 --> 00:34:45,708
<i>We're heading home now.</i>

722
00:34:45,792 --> 00:34:49,378
<i>Tomorrow's going to be a super early day.</i>

723
00:34:49,462 --> 00:34:53,091
<i>We'll be up at 5am to get ready.</i>

724
00:34:53,174 --> 00:34:57,261
<i>We're doing our own makeup.</i>

725
00:34:57,345 --> 00:35:00,807
<i>Not the uniform!</i>

726
00:35:00,890 --> 00:35:02,642
<i>I'll just check it out.</i>

727
00:35:03,684 --> 00:35:04,894
<i>Yes, you have to pay for it.</i>

728
00:35:04,977 --> 00:35:07,730
<i>It costs money! Save up for it!</i>

729
00:35:09,107 --> 00:35:12,902
- [chuckles]
<i>- Just make sure you do well in school.</i>

730
00:35:13,778 --> 00:35:19,283
- Who are you talking to?
<i>- Hi, guys! I'm on a call with my family.</i>

731
00:35:19,367 --> 00:35:26,374
[soft music playing]

732
00:35:36,467 --> 00:35:38,469
[Maloi] During downtime,
like water breaks,

733
00:35:38,553 --> 00:35:40,388
I'd go to my room and cry my eyes out.

734
00:35:40,471 --> 00:35:43,474
I was homesick.

735
00:35:43,558 --> 00:35:48,896
I'm used to living in a crowded house
with my siblings and parents.

736
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:51,816
Now, I'm not with them anymore,
so it was sort of a shock.

737
00:35:54,569 --> 00:35:57,572
<i>Hi, guys! It's Monday.</i>

738
00:35:57,655 --> 00:35:58,865
<i>Um...</i>

739
00:35:58,948 --> 00:36:01,492
<i>We have no time to chill,</i>

740
00:36:01,576 --> 00:36:05,079
<i>that's why my day is so productive.</i>

741
00:36:05,163 --> 00:36:08,166
<i>I didn't get enough rest.</i>

742
00:36:08,249 --> 00:36:09,876
<i>- Good morning!</i>
- [Gwen] <i>No.</i>

743
00:36:09,959 --> 00:36:12,795
<i>- Good morning!
- I don't want to say it's good.</i>

744
00:36:12,879 --> 00:36:15,882
<i>My gosh! Why are you like that?</i>

745
00:36:15,965 --> 00:36:17,800
<i>They're still in bed.</i>

746
00:36:17,884 --> 00:36:19,468
<i>Good morning, Stacey!</i>

747
00:36:19,552 --> 00:36:22,054
<i>Good morning!</i>

748
00:36:22,138 --> 00:36:24,056
<i>Let's annoy Mikha!</i>

749
00:36:26,559 --> 00:36:28,686
<i>Wow! She's beautiful
even when she's asleep.</i>

750
00:36:28,769 --> 00:36:29,979
[Mikha] A lot of the girls,

751
00:36:30,062 --> 00:36:33,858
including me, were depressed.

752
00:36:33,941 --> 00:36:36,068
And I got addicted to video games too.

753
00:36:36,152 --> 00:36:38,112
That was all I did most of the time.

754
00:36:38,196 --> 00:36:42,867
<i>Hi! I'm outside right now.</i>

755
00:36:44,285 --> 00:36:47,496
<i>It feels good to relax here.</i>

756
00:36:47,580 --> 00:36:48,873
<i>The view is nice.</i>

757
00:36:48,956 --> 00:36:52,793
[Jhoanna] It wasn't until after two months
that I started to feel the blues.

758
00:36:52,877 --> 00:36:55,129
I was like, "Oh, so
that's what it feels like."

759
00:36:55,213 --> 00:36:56,631
It wasn't all fun and games.

760
00:36:56,714 --> 00:37:01,177
[morose music playing]

761
00:37:01,260 --> 00:37:03,679
[Gwen] It was tough. I'm amazed
we survived all that drama.

762
00:37:03,763 --> 00:37:05,681
There were so many fights,
misunderstandings,

763
00:37:05,765 --> 00:37:07,099
and arguments.

764
00:37:07,183 --> 00:37:08,976
We had to adjust with each other.

765
00:37:09,060 --> 00:37:12,063
<i>Hi, guys, good morning!
So, I just got out of bed.</i>

766
00:37:12,146 --> 00:37:14,440
<i>Obviously, the girls woke me up.</i>

767
00:37:14,523 --> 00:37:15,399
<i>Oh my gosh!</i>

768
00:37:15,483 --> 00:37:16,776
<i>But I'm not the last.</i>

769
00:37:16,859 --> 00:37:19,237
<i>Mikha woke up later than I did.</i>

770
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:23,282
<i>- It was her! She woke me up!
- Shut up.</i>

771
00:37:23,366 --> 00:37:24,992
<i>Fine!</i> [laughs]

772
00:37:25,076 --> 00:37:27,870
[laughing]

773
00:37:27,954 --> 00:37:29,622
<i>You are not welcome here!</i>

774
00:37:29,705 --> 00:37:32,708
<i>You see how rude they are to me?</i>

775
00:37:32,792 --> 00:37:34,961
[Colet] I have siblings,
so I'm used to the chaos.

776
00:37:35,044 --> 00:37:37,380
The only difference
is we're all girls here.

777
00:37:37,463 --> 00:37:40,007
So we're all crazy like that. [laughs]

778
00:37:40,091 --> 00:37:43,636
Colet and Mikha have strong personalities.

779
00:37:43,719 --> 00:37:45,554
Stacey, on the other hand, likes to rant.

780
00:37:45,638 --> 00:37:48,015
But when confronted, she won't say a word.

781
00:37:48,099 --> 00:37:50,685
Jhoanna and I had a falling out before.

782
00:37:50,768 --> 00:37:51,894
If I remember correctly,
I was bullying her.

783
00:37:51,978 --> 00:37:54,480
[singing]

784
00:37:54,563 --> 00:37:56,399
[screaming]

785
00:37:56,482 --> 00:38:00,278
[laughing]

786
00:38:00,361 --> 00:38:02,571
[Jhoanna] My actions get
misinterpreted all the time.

787
00:38:02,655 --> 00:38:04,532
Like if I'm loud, I'm an attention-seeker.

788
00:38:04,615 --> 00:38:07,285
<i>It's Maloi.</i>

789
00:38:07,368 --> 00:38:09,495
<i>Jhoanna sounds like
she's doing a newscast.</i>

790
00:38:09,578 --> 00:38:11,872
Well, that's how I am. What can I do?

791
00:38:11,956 --> 00:38:18,587
[somber music playing]

792
00:38:20,214 --> 00:38:21,882
<i>Hello, anyone there? Help us! Help us!</i>

793
00:38:21,966 --> 00:38:23,467
<i>We're calling your attention.</i>

794
00:38:23,551 --> 00:38:25,261
<i>Aah!</i>

795
00:38:26,178 --> 00:38:29,390
<i>Water's coming in!</i>

796
00:38:29,473 --> 00:38:31,684
<i>The room is still a mess.</i>

797
00:38:31,767 --> 00:38:35,187
Imagine living with eight
different kinds of girls.

798
00:38:35,271 --> 00:38:36,772
Bringing them together
is already a challenge.

799
00:38:36,856 --> 00:38:40,067
But to have them live together
for two or three years? Come on!

800
00:38:40,151 --> 00:38:42,320
<i>Hi, guys! It's Tuesday!</i>

801
00:38:42,403 --> 00:38:43,529
<i>It's Thursday.</i>

802
00:38:43,612 --> 00:38:44,780
<i>Let me compose my thoughts.</i>

803
00:38:44,864 --> 00:38:46,615
<i>I have so much on my mind.</i>

804
00:38:46,699 --> 00:38:48,034
<i>I miss my family.</i>

805
00:38:48,117 --> 00:38:52,371
[somber music playing]

806
00:38:52,455 --> 00:38:54,290
We felt like we were going crazy

807
00:38:54,373 --> 00:38:56,584
because we've been stuck
inside the house for so long.

808
00:38:56,667 --> 00:38:58,085
We're doing the same
routine over and over.

809
00:38:58,169 --> 00:38:59,420
We're all sick of it.

810
00:38:59,503 --> 00:39:01,797
Plus, we're not sure if this
would lead to something.

811
00:39:02,548 --> 00:39:04,467
<i>Oh my gosh!</i>

812
00:39:07,261 --> 00:39:09,430
<i>Sorry, I need to stop.</i>

813
00:39:10,389 --> 00:39:12,475
<i>Go to the restroom first.</i>

814
00:39:16,854 --> 00:39:20,274
[overlapping chatter]

815
00:39:20,358 --> 00:39:25,780
[Colet] I think "exhausting"
is not enough to describe it.

816
00:39:25,863 --> 00:39:28,616
Our training was intense that
words can't even describe it.

817
00:39:28,699 --> 00:39:29,700
We did every kind of dance.

818
00:39:29,784 --> 00:39:32,286
And then there was the 20-to-1 workout.

819
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:33,996
Plus, the drills were off the charts!

820
00:39:34,080 --> 00:39:37,291
We also had to do stretching.
We tried everything.

821
00:39:37,375 --> 00:39:38,417
<i>It's showtime!</i>

822
00:39:38,501 --> 00:39:40,169
<i>Good morning!</i>

823
00:39:40,252 --> 00:39:41,629
<i>Good morning!</i>

824
00:39:45,091 --> 00:39:48,552
They wake up in the morning to train.

825
00:39:50,471 --> 00:39:52,598
[groaning]

826
00:39:52,681 --> 00:39:56,352
And then they have voice
lessons in the afternoon.

827
00:39:56,435 --> 00:40:02,400
[vocalizing]

828
00:40:02,483 --> 00:40:05,403
When that's done, they will prepare for...

829
00:40:05,486 --> 00:40:08,280
<i>So, catch us in our Kumu Live later.</i>

830
00:40:08,364 --> 00:40:11,575
<i>As you can see, I'm wearing
an ankle support.</i>

831
00:40:14,370 --> 00:40:21,377
[overlapping chatter]

832
00:40:25,256 --> 00:40:27,383
Most of the time, we'd ask ourselves,

833
00:40:27,466 --> 00:40:29,635
"Why are we doing this? What is it for?"

834
00:40:29,718 --> 00:40:31,387
They'd ask "Coach, when will
we be famous?"

835
00:40:31,470 --> 00:40:33,264
They told me they'd
settle for doing a show

836
00:40:33,347 --> 00:40:35,975
in a small mall or something like that.

837
00:40:36,058 --> 00:40:37,101
We didn't have the funds.

838
00:40:37,184 --> 00:40:39,645
We have yet to see
any returns on this project.

839
00:40:39,728 --> 00:40:42,565
Our YouTube views were really low.

840
00:40:42,648 --> 00:40:45,317
We're lucky if we'd get 5,000
to 7,000 views.

841
00:40:45,401 --> 00:40:48,070
So we were worried that
if it's not going to fly,

842
00:40:50,072 --> 00:40:52,158
then we might have to make the tough call.

843
00:40:55,661 --> 00:40:57,788
[Noli] <i>Even though the license
was not renewed...</i>

844
00:40:57,872 --> 00:41:01,083
<i>They can't air on Channel 2.</i>

845
00:41:01,167 --> 00:41:04,128
<i>...with thousands losing
their jobs in the process.</i>

846
00:41:04,211 --> 00:41:06,464
<i>The National Telecommunications Commission</i>

847
00:41:06,547 --> 00:41:08,382
<i>did not grant the license</i>

848
00:41:08,466 --> 00:41:12,803
<i>for ABS-CBN's continued operations
on free-to-air television.</i>

849
00:41:12,887 --> 00:41:14,930
The next challenge was the shutdown.

850
00:41:15,014 --> 00:41:16,849
And after that, retrenchment.

851
00:41:18,309 --> 00:41:21,395
<i>We're signing...</i> [laughter]

852
00:41:21,479 --> 00:41:23,481
<i>the BINIverse posters.</i>

853
00:41:23,564 --> 00:41:25,983
<i>You see, we don't sign and mass print.</i>

854
00:41:26,066 --> 00:41:27,067
<i>We sign every single poster.</i>

855
00:41:27,151 --> 00:41:30,196
<i>Of course, we feel tired
but we're excited.</i>

856
00:41:30,279 --> 00:41:33,365
<i>We're more excited than tired.</i>

857
00:41:38,662 --> 00:41:42,541
We carried on with the training
while trying to keep updated

858
00:41:42,625 --> 00:41:45,753
on whether ABS-CBN will get
its franchise renewed or not.

859
00:41:45,836 --> 00:41:47,838
<i>Right. Left.</i>

860
00:41:49,465 --> 00:41:51,675
Then the company president
made the announcement

861
00:41:51,759 --> 00:41:53,260
that we were shutting down.

862
00:41:53,344 --> 00:41:55,679
The screen went to color bars
or something.

863
00:41:55,763 --> 00:41:57,890
I remember my first question
to Director Lauren was,

864
00:41:57,973 --> 00:42:00,643
"What will happen to the girls?"

865
00:42:00,726 --> 00:42:04,605
It reached a point that we had to discuss
if we should pursue the project or not.

866
00:42:04,688 --> 00:42:11,570
When the network shut down,
we were all staring at the TV.

867
00:42:11,654 --> 00:42:15,741
I was like, "Should I go home now?"

868
00:42:18,035 --> 00:42:19,662
I mean, we just got started.

869
00:42:19,745 --> 00:42:23,749
We haven't even shown our skills yet
and it's over just like that.

870
00:42:23,832 --> 00:42:26,627
They've spent so much money on us
without getting any profits.

871
00:42:26,710 --> 00:42:30,881
So I've kind of accepted that our group
could be dropped anytime.

872
00:42:30,965 --> 00:42:32,675
[Maloi] We've made a lot of sacrifices.

873
00:42:32,758 --> 00:42:35,844
Our time, our effort, our health.

874
00:42:35,928 --> 00:42:42,560
At that moment, we just laid in a circle
while holding hands and wept.

875
00:42:44,061 --> 00:42:47,398
We said everything we wanted to say.

876
00:42:47,481 --> 00:42:49,400
We let it all out.

877
00:42:49,483 --> 00:42:53,153
We told ourselves
that no matter what happens,

878
00:42:53,237 --> 00:42:55,864
we'll get through this.

879
00:42:55,948 --> 00:42:59,368
That's when I realized
that crying won't do any good.

880
00:42:59,451 --> 00:43:01,912
We had to be tough.

881
00:43:01,996 --> 00:43:04,873
[somber music playing]

882
00:43:04,957 --> 00:43:06,166
When the management called for a meeting,

883
00:43:06,250 --> 00:43:10,379
we were expecting them to say
that they were abandoning the project.

884
00:43:10,462 --> 00:43:11,547
But no...

885
00:43:11,630 --> 00:43:14,008
They said they will continue it.

886
00:43:14,091 --> 00:43:15,926
They decided to continue
supporting the project.

887
00:43:16,010 --> 00:43:17,303
The girls were like,

888
00:43:17,386 --> 00:43:20,681
"Come on. Let's keep going.
Let's push through this!"

889
00:43:20,764 --> 00:43:22,099
Life goes on. That's how it is.

890
00:43:22,182 --> 00:43:25,394
Just continue what you're doing
until someone tells you to stop.

891
00:43:25,477 --> 00:43:27,980
[singing] <i>♪ And no matter what
They say to break us ♪</i>

892
00:43:28,063 --> 00:43:30,274
<i>♪ Take our spirits down ♪</i>

893
00:43:30,357 --> 00:43:34,987
<i>♪ We just need to look around ♪</i>

894
00:43:35,070 --> 00:43:38,198
<i>♪ Now here with you ♪</i>

895
00:43:38,282 --> 00:43:39,783
<i>♪ Found something new ♪</i>

896
00:43:39,867 --> 00:43:42,578
<i>♪ Through the dark nights The highlights ♪</i>

897
00:43:42,661 --> 00:43:46,206
<i>♪ You're my lifeline
As we take our flight ♪</i>

898
00:43:46,290 --> 00:43:50,961
<i>♪ Oh oh oh oh oh ♪</i>

899
00:44:01,805 --> 00:44:03,390
Actually, they have the same tempo.

900
00:44:03,474 --> 00:44:05,392
<i>- Oh.</i>
- This one is softer.

901
00:44:05,476 --> 00:44:07,478
Do you want to make it slower?

902
00:44:07,561 --> 00:44:10,356
Well, this part seems okay.

903
00:44:12,816 --> 00:44:14,693
[Anna] When I first watched them,
I wasn't too confident.

904
00:44:14,777 --> 00:44:18,072
I was thinking,
"Not all of them can sing."

905
00:44:18,155 --> 00:44:24,411
I was worried about how I'd train them
to make them better singers.

906
00:44:24,495 --> 00:44:25,704
<i>One, two, three.</i>

907
00:44:26,038 --> 00:44:32,961
[singing "Magdamag"]

908
00:44:33,045 --> 00:44:34,880
<i>Game, girls. Let's go.</i>

909
00:44:34,963 --> 00:44:41,970
[soft music playing]

910
00:44:45,933 --> 00:44:49,019
What you see on camera

911
00:44:49,103 --> 00:44:52,022
is pretty much what happens
behind the scenes too.

912
00:44:52,106 --> 00:44:54,316
The girls' relationship is very solid

913
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:56,819
that they don't have to hide
anything in front of the camera.

914
00:44:57,569 --> 00:44:58,862
<i>It's showtime!</i>

915
00:44:58,946 --> 00:45:03,992
[soft music playing]

916
00:45:04,076 --> 00:45:07,413
<i>They hit the pool
and Aiah went for a swim too.</i>

917
00:45:07,496 --> 00:45:08,789
<i>I don't know if you can see her.</i>

918
00:45:08,872 --> 00:45:10,874
<i>Oh, there. Look at her go.</i>

919
00:45:10,958 --> 00:45:13,127
[Gwen] We stayed together
under one roof for a while,

920
00:45:13,210 --> 00:45:14,545
and we've all grown up and matured.

921
00:45:14,628 --> 00:45:16,046
That's the best part.

922
00:45:16,130 --> 00:45:18,382
They all learned how
to adjust to each other

923
00:45:18,465 --> 00:45:19,675
so that they can blend well together.

924
00:45:19,758 --> 00:45:21,844
It's the same with their friendship.

925
00:45:21,927 --> 00:45:25,431
They know when someone is upset
or going through something.

926
00:45:25,514 --> 00:45:30,894
They give them space
before trying to fix things.

927
00:45:30,978 --> 00:45:36,108
It's nice to see how they've all kind of
matured throughout the years.

928
00:45:36,191 --> 00:45:42,990
[singing "Lagi"]

929
00:46:01,550 --> 00:46:03,302
<i>Ah.</i> [clears throat]

930
00:46:04,636 --> 00:46:07,181
[singing] <i>♪ Nothing can hold us back ♪</i>

931
00:46:07,264 --> 00:46:09,016
It was the morning of August 20.

932
00:46:09,099 --> 00:46:11,977
Ms. Jovy called for a Zoom meeting.

933
00:46:12,060 --> 00:46:14,396
I just woke up at that time.

934
00:46:14,480 --> 00:46:16,773
It wasn't even 6am yet.
It was still early.

935
00:46:16,857 --> 00:46:21,904
Her mom went into a coma after a surgery.

936
00:46:21,987 --> 00:46:26,867
We found out about it during the lockdown.

937
00:46:26,950 --> 00:46:29,286
I felt something was off.
That there's something wrong.

938
00:46:29,369 --> 00:46:33,081
Who in their right mind calls
for a Zoom meeting at 5am?

939
00:46:33,165 --> 00:46:35,083
It has to be something important.

940
00:46:35,167 --> 00:46:37,127
Turns out, it really was.

941
00:46:37,211 --> 00:46:43,091
<i>Sheena, I don't know how to...</i>

942
00:46:43,175 --> 00:46:48,180
<i>I just wanted to tell you that...</i>

943
00:46:48,263 --> 00:46:54,686
<i>We're very sorry, but your mom
passed away this morning.</i>

944
00:46:54,770 --> 00:46:57,272
[Sheena] Sir Rayms said that
my mom is gone.

945
00:46:57,356 --> 00:47:00,484
It didn't sink in at first.

946
00:47:00,567 --> 00:47:01,902
I didn't even cry during the Zoom call.

947
00:47:01,985 --> 00:47:04,696
I was just staring into space.
I was like, "Okay."

948
00:47:04,780 --> 00:47:08,200
After that, I locked myself
in the room and cried.

949
00:47:08,283 --> 00:47:11,203
The girls kept knocking,
but I locked the door.

950
00:47:11,286 --> 00:47:13,997
Eventually, I felt bad for them
and opened the door.

951
00:47:14,081 --> 00:47:16,291
There was nothing we could do.

952
00:47:16,375 --> 00:47:21,463
So we just let her cry and
tried to make her feel better.

953
00:47:22,756 --> 00:47:24,800
[Stacey] It felt like we also lost a mom.

954
00:47:24,883 --> 00:47:30,597
Sheena's like our baby,
so we look out for her.

955
00:47:30,681 --> 00:47:34,685
When she found out her mom was sick,
we were still in training.

956
00:47:34,768 --> 00:47:38,105
She was wondering why her mom
stopped messaging her.

957
00:47:38,188 --> 00:47:43,610
So we saw how it started,
and we witnessed how it ended too.

958
00:47:43,694 --> 00:47:45,070
<i>Sheena!</i>

959
00:47:45,153 --> 00:47:48,365
<i>I'm going to miss you so much!</i>

960
00:47:50,367 --> 00:47:52,828
<i>- Ew!
- I'm going to miss you.</i>

961
00:47:54,371 --> 00:47:56,665
<i>I'm going home.</i>

962
00:47:56,748 --> 00:47:58,166
In my head, I thought I'd
be home in no time.

963
00:47:58,250 --> 00:48:00,377
Like, I was planning
to travel the same night.

964
00:48:00,460 --> 00:48:03,338
But no, there was a ton of paperwork.

965
00:48:03,964 --> 00:48:05,757
We still have a long way to go.

966
00:48:05,841 --> 00:48:08,635
I'm getting carsick. [chuckles]

967
00:48:12,764 --> 00:48:15,517
[Sheena] Before I could go home,

968
00:48:15,601 --> 00:48:17,894
I had to quarantine in a hotel.

969
00:48:17,978 --> 00:48:20,230
Oh look, Grandma's here.

970
00:48:23,859 --> 00:48:25,819
Stop. Don't cry.

971
00:48:25,902 --> 00:48:29,281
You've gotten so big! [Sheena laughs]

972
00:48:29,364 --> 00:48:30,741
You've gotten so big.

973
00:48:30,824 --> 00:48:34,745
Hello! Welcome home, honey!
Sheena! [chuckles]

974
00:48:35,579 --> 00:48:38,415
I love you! I missed you so much!

975
00:48:38,498 --> 00:48:42,044
She didn't make it in time to see her mom.

976
00:48:44,087 --> 00:48:47,966
By the time she got home,
her mom was already buried.

977
00:48:48,050 --> 00:48:54,431
[melancholic music continues]

978
00:48:54,514 --> 00:48:57,184
Next up is, of course, my mother,

979
00:48:57,267 --> 00:49:00,520
my mommy, Angeline M. Catacutan.

980
00:49:00,604 --> 00:49:05,275
People mistake us for siblings.
I wonder why?

981
00:49:06,985 --> 00:49:08,070
Yeah. It's true.

982
00:49:08,153 --> 00:49:11,531
My mom was my go-to person.

983
00:49:14,368 --> 00:49:19,915
[Maloi] Sheena's really one of the
strongest people I've ever met.

984
00:49:19,998 --> 00:49:22,459
The way she chooses to keep pushing...

985
00:49:22,542 --> 00:49:25,045
That's very inspiring.

986
00:49:25,128 --> 00:49:26,296
Sheena's so young,

987
00:49:26,380 --> 00:49:28,590
but she's already been through a lot.

988
00:49:28,674 --> 00:49:32,511
As her older sisters, as much as possible

989
00:49:33,261 --> 00:49:35,764
[Maloi] Sheena. Sheena.

990
00:49:35,847 --> 00:49:37,974
[giggles]

991
00:49:38,058 --> 00:49:40,268
- Oh my god, how scary.
- [both laugh]

992
00:49:40,352 --> 00:49:46,316
We try to have fun when we're together
so she can still somehow enjoy her youth.

993
00:49:46,400 --> 00:49:48,902
[Korean audio prompt]
<i>Up, down, up, up, down.</i>

994
00:49:48,985 --> 00:49:53,198
[Sheena laughs]

995
00:49:53,281 --> 00:49:55,075
When I got back from Isabela,

996
00:49:55,158 --> 00:49:59,454
I felt like they really
missed me and cared for me.

997
00:49:59,538 --> 00:50:01,998
That's when our bond really grew stronger

998
00:50:02,082 --> 00:50:05,794
because we had no one
to lean on but each other.

999
00:50:07,963 --> 00:50:10,465
[Jhoanna] People usually
think that in girl groups,

1000
00:50:10,549 --> 00:50:14,052
it's all about competition,
jealousy, and backstabbing.

1001
00:50:14,136 --> 00:50:16,680
Well, we kind of went through
that phase too,

1002
00:50:16,763 --> 00:50:20,267
but now it's like
a totally different story.

1003
00:50:20,350 --> 00:50:22,102
[Mikha] I appreciated the fact
that we stayed together

1004
00:50:22,185 --> 00:50:24,062
in one place for a long time.

1005
00:50:24,146 --> 00:50:27,274
Because I feel like that's what
made our bond this strong.

1006
00:50:27,357 --> 00:50:30,610
[Aiah] We learned how to make
the most of living together.

1007
00:50:30,694 --> 00:50:33,572
That time, I'd rather have that
than to be alone.

1008
00:50:33,655 --> 00:50:36,992
I'm happy because God
gave me seven sisters.

1009
00:50:37,075 --> 00:50:39,870
BINI, these seven girls,

1010
00:50:41,371 --> 00:50:43,582
they are the highlight of my life.

1011
00:50:44,374 --> 00:50:45,292
[sniffles]

1012
00:50:45,375 --> 00:50:47,586
When I'm old and gray,

1013
00:50:47,669 --> 00:50:51,256
this is one of the stories I
will be telling everyone about.

1014
00:50:52,382 --> 00:50:56,636
I'm so grateful to have shared
this journey with them.

1015
00:50:57,554 --> 00:50:59,097
So grateful.

1016
00:50:59,181 --> 00:51:02,350
[sniffles, sobs]

1017
00:51:05,061 --> 00:51:07,397
[Gwen] If you ask me, I
don't really have a best friend.

1018
00:51:07,481 --> 00:51:10,066
I used to struggle with
those kinds of things a lot,

1019
00:51:10,150 --> 00:51:12,486
but now I'm so lucky to have these girls.

1020
00:51:12,569 --> 00:51:16,782
They're my rock. I know I
can always count on them,

1021
00:51:16,865 --> 00:51:19,201
no matter what. They're my constant.

1022
00:51:19,284 --> 00:51:22,579
[singing] <i>Happy birthday to you</i>

1023
00:51:22,662 --> 00:51:24,998
<i>So that's why there was
a camera as I was going out.</i>

1024
00:51:25,081 --> 00:51:28,251
[singing] <i>Happy birthday to you</i>

1025
00:51:28,335 --> 00:51:31,463
[cheering]

1026
00:51:31,546 --> 00:51:33,632
<i>I knew something was weird.</i>

1027
00:51:34,883 --> 00:51:37,302
[Reden] The girls always go
the extra mile for birthdays.

1028
00:51:37,385 --> 00:51:38,678
They really put in the effort.

1029
00:51:38,762 --> 00:51:42,974
That's when I knew they
considered each other family.

1030
00:51:43,767 --> 00:51:46,478
<i>Happy birthday!</i>

1031
00:51:46,561 --> 00:51:48,980
<i>- Aww! Happy birthday!
- Yay!</i>

1032
00:51:49,064 --> 00:51:51,775
<i>- Happy birthday!
- Aww!</i>

1033
00:51:51,858 --> 00:51:54,069
<i>It's so yummy!</i>

1034
00:51:54,152 --> 00:51:58,073
[indistinct chatter]

1035
00:51:58,156 --> 00:52:00,659
[singing "Na Na Na"]
Seven, eight, and "na".

1036
00:52:01,785 --> 00:52:04,162
Five, six, seven, eight, and...

1037
00:52:04,246 --> 00:52:05,497
["Na Na Na" playing]

1038
00:52:05,580 --> 00:52:07,791
[cheering]

1039
00:52:07,874 --> 00:52:12,420
["Na Na Na" continues]

1040
00:52:12,504 --> 00:52:14,589
For Jhoanna...

1041
00:52:14,673 --> 00:52:18,093
when you hear the line
"about music, art, fashion,"

1042
00:52:18,176 --> 00:52:20,178
that's your cue to go to the back.

1043
00:52:20,262 --> 00:52:22,597
So, just a few reminders:
for Stacey's portion,

1044
00:52:22,681 --> 00:52:24,683
let's give her time to get changed.

1045
00:52:24,766 --> 00:52:26,685
Stretch that part. Okay?

1046
00:52:26,768 --> 00:52:28,353
[Mikha] It's the first time
we've actually,

1047
00:52:28,436 --> 00:52:30,480
like ran everything through.

1048
00:52:30,564 --> 00:52:34,776
And this is the closest we have been
to being complete.

1049
00:52:34,860 --> 00:52:36,862
It's finally coming, you know.

1050
00:52:36,945 --> 00:52:39,948
It finally dawned on us.

1051
00:52:40,031 --> 00:52:42,409
[Colet] It hasn't hit me yet
that there are only two days left.

1052
00:52:42,492 --> 00:52:44,578
When we were just standing here,

1053
00:52:44,661 --> 00:52:47,664
I was doing this with
my hands behind my back.

1054
00:52:47,747 --> 00:52:50,500
I was so tense, I don't know why.

1055
00:52:50,584 --> 00:52:52,002
I even made the sign of
the cross a few times

1056
00:52:52,085 --> 00:52:53,712
right before I went on.

1057
00:52:53,795 --> 00:52:58,550
It was also a big challenge to figure out
how to introduce them.

1058
00:53:01,553 --> 00:53:04,806
[MQ] What's BINI? Why were they formed?

1059
00:53:04,890 --> 00:53:08,018
Those are the friendly questions,
and I don't mind answering those.

1060
00:53:08,101 --> 00:53:10,896
But then there are the ones
that are just straight-up rude, like,

1061
00:53:10,979 --> 00:53:13,064
'Who the heck are they?' [laughs]

1062
00:53:13,148 --> 00:53:16,192
We made several attempts,
different experiments

1063
00:53:16,276 --> 00:53:19,613
on what kind of music we wanted for BINI.

1064
00:53:19,696 --> 00:53:24,659
Let's talk about their pre-debut single,
<i>Da Coconut Nut,</i> okay? [laughs]

1065
00:53:24,743 --> 00:53:26,494
That coconut song was something else.

1066
00:53:26,578 --> 00:53:28,955
To begin with, the song is cute.
And I'm not cute.

1067
00:53:29,039 --> 00:53:30,582
[Maloi] <i>Da Coconut Nut</i>
was all we rehearsed

1068
00:53:30,665 --> 00:53:32,000
for nine whole months.

1069
00:53:32,083 --> 00:53:33,877
I swear I could dance to it in my sleep,

1070
00:53:33,960 --> 00:53:36,212
That's how much we practiced it.

1071
00:53:36,296 --> 00:53:37,672
We didn't have a stylist.

1072
00:53:37,756 --> 00:53:39,341
The girls upcycled their own costumes.

1073
00:53:39,424 --> 00:53:40,842
<i>Hey, let's continue this later.</i>

1074
00:53:41,551 --> 00:53:43,303
<i>We have to shoot the video.
They need it by 8 p.m.</i>

1075
00:53:43,386 --> 00:53:44,763
During my <i>Da Coconut Nut</i> era,

1076
00:53:44,846 --> 00:53:46,473
I was super stressed out.

1077
00:53:46,556 --> 00:53:47,974
I had a boil here on my forehead

1078
00:53:48,058 --> 00:53:49,809
and another on my cheek.

1079
00:53:49,893 --> 00:53:51,770
We had very limited resources.

1080
00:53:51,853 --> 00:53:53,563
So our costumes were DIY.

1081
00:53:53,647 --> 00:53:56,816
We got a bunch of stuff
from Coach Mickey's wife and Miss MQ.

1082
00:53:56,900 --> 00:53:58,693
When I think about
how we looked back then,

1083
00:53:58,777 --> 00:54:00,320
it was total cringe!

1084
00:54:00,403 --> 00:54:03,114
I didn't imagine that <i>Da Coconut Nut</i>
would turn out that way.

1085
00:54:03,198 --> 00:54:04,199
You know, since they're a new girl group,

1086
00:54:04,282 --> 00:54:07,452
you kind of expect
their song to be badass.

1087
00:54:07,535 --> 00:54:09,287
Then, they came out with <i>Da Coconut Nut.</i>

1088
00:54:09,371 --> 00:54:11,539
So, people were like, "What on earth?"

1089
00:54:12,582 --> 00:54:14,876
<i>Take a look at this face.</i>

1090
00:54:14,960 --> 00:54:17,671
<i>I will make my debut with this face.</i>

1091
00:54:17,754 --> 00:54:22,008
So, they didn't catch
people's interest at that time.

1092
00:54:22,092 --> 00:54:23,259
<i>Hello!</i>

1093
00:54:23,343 --> 00:54:25,261
[MQ] There were so many
bashers hating on them

1094
00:54:25,345 --> 00:54:28,306
saying that they were too plain
or something like that.

1095
00:54:28,390 --> 00:54:33,395
These people will never know
the sacrifices we had to make

1096
00:54:33,478 --> 00:54:35,271
to get the girls up to that point.

1097
00:54:35,355 --> 00:54:37,315
[Maloi] There are so many
memories tied to that song.

1098
00:54:37,399 --> 00:54:39,150
All the struggles we went through,

1099
00:54:39,234 --> 00:54:41,945
tears we shed together,
and all those things.

1100
00:54:42,028 --> 00:54:43,613
We're so used to being
in front of the camera.

1101
00:54:43,697 --> 00:54:48,576
It felt like all we did was
shoot performance videos.

1102
00:54:48,660 --> 00:54:51,621
[upbeat music playing]

1103
00:54:51,705 --> 00:54:53,081
We only had one camera.

1104
00:54:53,164 --> 00:54:54,541
So, we'd end up doing
the same dance routine

1105
00:54:54,624 --> 00:54:56,835
over and over to get different angles.

1106
00:54:56,918 --> 00:54:59,379
Launching a new group
during COVID is no joke.

1107
00:54:59,462 --> 00:55:01,256
On top of that, they're performers.

1108
00:55:01,339 --> 00:55:03,258
Like, where would they perform?

1109
00:55:03,341 --> 00:55:05,468
We had no music shows anymore.

1110
00:55:05,552 --> 00:55:10,890
We were still figuring out what direction
we wanted to take this musically.

1111
00:55:10,974 --> 00:55:13,059
Should they be sweet or edgy?

1112
00:55:13,143 --> 00:55:14,728
What songs do people prefer?

1113
00:55:14,811 --> 00:55:16,438
Filipino or English?

1114
00:55:16,521 --> 00:55:20,150
We had no designated makeup artist before.

1115
00:55:20,233 --> 00:55:23,278
But then Ic's came along
as our visual director.

1116
00:55:25,655 --> 00:55:27,824
[Ica] I first met the girls when
I was asked do their styling

1117
00:55:27,907 --> 00:55:29,784
for their first variety show performance.

1118
00:55:29,868 --> 00:55:32,829
That's the vibe we visualized
for BINI's branding.

1119
00:55:32,912 --> 00:55:34,831
We wanted to make them super relatable.

1120
00:55:34,914 --> 00:55:36,708
If everything can be thrifted,
we're totally down.

1121
00:55:36,791 --> 00:55:43,673
After all, we drew inspiration
from unique styles of Filipino icons.

1122
00:55:43,757 --> 00:55:46,801
She's the one who really
defined our brand,

1123
00:55:46,885 --> 00:55:48,803
our outfits, and overall look.

1124
00:55:48,887 --> 00:55:54,851
[indistinct chatter]

1125
00:56:01,733 --> 00:56:05,695
[MQ] In the beginning,
it was tough to sell BINI.

1126
00:56:05,779 --> 00:56:07,072
They had eight members,

1127
00:56:07,155 --> 00:56:09,032
so people found it hard
to tell them apart at first.

1128
00:56:09,115 --> 00:56:10,533
People thought everyone
just looked the same

1129
00:56:10,617 --> 00:56:14,287
because they didn't know them yet.

1130
00:56:14,370 --> 00:56:19,375
When we had a listening
session for their debut song,

1131
00:56:19,459 --> 00:56:21,419
the runaway winner was <i>Born to Win.</i>

1132
00:56:21,503 --> 00:56:27,967
[singing "Born To Win" acapella]

1133
00:56:33,807 --> 00:56:35,975
[Sheena] We had full glam, hair,
makeup, and complete outfits.

1134
00:56:36,059 --> 00:56:38,103
It was a total game-changer.

1135
00:56:38,186 --> 00:56:40,355
It was a complete 360 from
our <i>Da Coconut Nut</i> days.

1136
00:56:40,438 --> 00:56:44,609
We were finally starting to
feel like a real girl group.

1137
00:56:49,989 --> 00:56:51,783
["Born To Win" playing] <i>BINI!</i>

1138
00:56:51,866 --> 00:56:54,327
Alright, this is it!

1139
00:56:54,410 --> 00:56:56,287
This is the song that's
going to make BINI blow up.

1140
00:56:58,581 --> 00:57:04,963
["Born To Win" continues]

1141
00:57:17,976 --> 00:57:21,062
[Mikha] People are all on social media
right now because of the pandemic.

1142
00:57:21,146 --> 00:57:24,023
It should have been easier
to promote the group.

1143
00:57:24,107 --> 00:57:26,651
But it wasn't. It was so hard.

1144
00:57:26,734 --> 00:57:28,111
Okay. Spoke too soon.

1145
00:57:28,194 --> 00:57:29,320
It's a whole different vibe

1146
00:57:29,404 --> 00:57:31,823
when you're performing
in front of a live audience.

1147
00:57:31,906 --> 00:57:34,200
It's just not the same
with just a handful of us.

1148
00:57:34,284 --> 00:57:40,832
This is when the OG fans
started to take notice of them.

1149
00:57:40,915 --> 00:57:42,834
At least for the first years of BINI,

1150
00:57:42,917 --> 00:57:45,211
it was really a trial and error.

1151
00:57:45,295 --> 00:57:49,424
You have to keep making songs
over and over again

1152
00:57:49,507 --> 00:57:53,970
hoping that one day, it'll become a hit.

1153
00:57:54,053 --> 00:57:57,223
["Na Na Na" playing]

1154
00:57:57,307 --> 00:58:02,854
["I Feel Good" playing]

1155
00:58:02,937 --> 00:58:05,398
[Stacey] We'd tell each other
"This will be a hit."

1156
00:58:05,482 --> 00:58:08,818
"This is our year, girls!"
We expected the song to blow up.

1157
00:58:09,611 --> 00:58:15,867
["Lagi" playing]

1158
00:58:17,327 --> 00:58:20,121
It did blow up in our faces. [chuckles]

1159
00:58:20,205 --> 00:58:22,999
Besides <i>Born to Win,</i>
we released so many songs.

1160
00:58:23,082 --> 00:58:27,879
["Golden Arrow" playing]

1161
00:58:27,962 --> 00:58:30,381
At that time, only our fans
listened to our songs.

1162
00:58:32,300 --> 00:58:34,928
["Pit A Pat" playing]

1163
00:58:35,011 --> 00:58:36,346
We are very grateful to them.

1164
00:58:36,429 --> 00:58:38,223
They're always there to support us

1165
00:58:38,306 --> 00:58:40,808
and they're the reason
why our streams and views keep increasing.

1166
00:58:40,892 --> 00:58:43,728
One million! Wow!

1167
00:58:43,811 --> 00:58:46,231
[squealing]

1168
00:58:46,314 --> 00:58:47,357
Then, suddenly, the pandemic ended,

1169
00:58:47,440 --> 00:58:51,986
and we had to figure out
how to interact with an audience.

1170
00:58:52,070 --> 00:58:56,533
[indistinct chatter]

1171
00:58:56,616 --> 00:59:01,037
Honestly, all I can think of
is seeing my family and friends.

1172
00:59:01,120 --> 00:59:02,247
I'm super motivated

1173
00:59:02,330 --> 00:59:05,750
because I'll finally see
my family again on the 28th!

1174
00:59:05,833 --> 00:59:10,588
I'm pumped because it's been forever
since we've all been together.

1175
00:59:10,672 --> 00:59:12,006
[indistinct chatter]

1176
00:59:12,090 --> 00:59:14,592
- Hi, Sir Roxy.
- Hello.

1177
00:59:14,676 --> 00:59:20,431
[indistinct chatter]

1178
00:59:20,515 --> 00:59:23,101
- Let's go.
- Aiah.

1179
00:59:23,685 --> 00:59:25,979
- Let's pray first.
- Aiah.

1180
00:59:28,231 --> 00:59:29,190
Lord.

1181
00:59:35,363 --> 00:59:37,198
[Man] Jho, you're on in a few minutes.

1182
00:59:37,282 --> 00:59:39,617
Tell me how you feel.

1183
00:59:39,701 --> 00:59:42,912
I'm freaking out!
Like I'm going to pee my pants!

1184
00:59:42,996 --> 00:59:43,913
[Man] Why?

1185
00:59:43,997 --> 00:59:46,708
Because Director Lauren
and Sir Roxy is here.

1186
00:59:46,791 --> 00:59:50,211
It feels like we're being evaluated again.

1187
00:59:50,295 --> 00:59:51,713
We can do this.

1188
00:59:51,796 --> 00:59:52,880
One, two, three!

1189
00:59:52,964 --> 00:59:54,215
- BINI-besties!
- BINI-besties!

1190
00:59:54,299 --> 00:59:57,385
[cheering]

1191
00:59:57,468 --> 00:59:59,137
[tense music playing]

1192
00:59:59,220 --> 01:00:02,599
[Mikha] We all felt like it was the
management presentation all over again,

1193
01:00:02,682 --> 01:00:04,809
as if we were up
for evaluation like before.

1194
01:00:04,892 --> 01:00:07,103
Memories of our trainee days
and the elimination

1195
01:00:07,186 --> 01:00:10,607
came rushing back to me.

1196
01:00:10,690 --> 01:00:14,819
[tense music continues]

1197
01:00:14,902 --> 01:00:17,113
[Lauren] I always felt I
needed to find a reason.

1198
01:00:17,196 --> 01:00:21,492
To me, I felt like it was
only a matter of time.

1199
01:00:21,576 --> 01:00:24,162
It was like we had the
perfect combination of people,

1200
01:00:24,245 --> 01:00:26,247
and the team was all on board.

1201
01:00:26,331 --> 01:00:29,876
The girls were well-trained.

1202
01:00:29,959 --> 01:00:34,547
So there was certainly some frustration
why we hadn't hit it big yet.

1203
01:00:34,631 --> 01:00:37,008
Back when we used to do events,

1204
01:00:37,091 --> 01:00:40,053
it felt like we were just another group,
nothing special.

1205
01:00:40,678 --> 01:00:43,014
- Ready, BINI?
- Yes!

1206
01:00:43,097 --> 01:00:44,682
We'd always hear people say

1207
01:00:44,766 --> 01:00:47,435
"They're really good, but who are they?"

1208
01:00:47,518 --> 01:00:49,979
I mean they knew the songs,
but not the girls.

1209
01:00:50,063 --> 01:00:53,066
We even had a hard time
reaching 100,000 views.

1210
01:00:53,149 --> 01:00:55,109
We were keeping tabs
on how long we've been training.

1211
01:00:55,193 --> 01:00:57,654
We'd been together two years
and still no success.

1212
01:01:02,492 --> 01:01:05,787
We were beginning to regret
all the sacrifices we made.

1213
01:01:05,870 --> 01:01:08,289
Like the time we spent
training were all for nothing.

1214
01:01:10,667 --> 01:01:13,127
[MQ] It was my job to market them.

1215
01:01:13,211 --> 01:01:17,340
There were brands that ignored us.

1216
01:01:17,423 --> 01:01:19,884
Of course,
I wanted them to earn something.

1217
01:01:19,967 --> 01:01:25,890
But sometimes they would get lowballed
or get asked to perform for free.

1218
01:01:25,973 --> 01:01:30,353
You see, we wanted people
to become aware of their group.

1219
01:01:30,436 --> 01:01:33,189
People would even say,
"Who do you think you are?"

1220
01:01:33,272 --> 01:01:35,692
You'll know who we are. We are BINI!

1221
01:01:35,775 --> 01:01:39,278
There were many events
where people looked bored,

1222
01:01:39,362 --> 01:01:41,406
or meet-and-greets
where people ignored us.

1223
01:01:41,489 --> 01:01:45,702
We would force a smile,
but deep inside... Ouch!

1224
01:01:45,785 --> 01:01:48,204
[chuckles] Hi!

1225
01:01:48,287 --> 01:01:50,289
[Stacey] Every time we had a gig,

1226
01:01:50,373 --> 01:01:54,961
we were always worried
if the Blooms would show up

1227
01:01:55,044 --> 01:01:56,295
or if anyone would recognize us.

1228
01:01:56,379 --> 01:02:00,717
One of the painful questions we'd ask was,
"Will anyone applaud us?"

1229
01:02:00,800 --> 01:02:03,344
I didn't want to question
why we hadn't blown up yet

1230
01:02:03,428 --> 01:02:04,429
after three years.

1231
01:02:04,512 --> 01:02:05,805
Guys, say hi!

1232
01:02:05,888 --> 01:02:09,183
Hi! [laughing]

1233
01:02:09,267 --> 01:02:12,061
[Ica] You'll get back
what you put out there.

1234
01:02:12,145 --> 01:02:14,272
Time went by very slowly for us.

1235
01:02:15,189 --> 01:02:20,486
This one was during
our appearance on <i>It's Showtime.</i>

1236
01:02:20,570 --> 01:02:21,863
[Reden] They struggled a lot.

1237
01:02:21,946 --> 01:02:24,240
I've witnessed their tears,

1238
01:02:24,323 --> 01:02:28,035
but I've also witnessed
their joy and hard work.

1239
01:02:28,119 --> 01:02:29,620
They've got great dynamics.

1240
01:02:29,704 --> 01:02:32,832
They're all working towards one thing.

1241
01:02:32,915 --> 01:02:35,001
I told myself it was possible.

1242
01:02:35,084 --> 01:02:37,211
They became sad, but they never gave up.

1243
01:02:37,295 --> 01:02:40,173
None of the girls
showed any signs of giving up.

1244
01:02:40,256 --> 01:02:42,592
You can't help but love them,

1245
01:02:42,675 --> 01:02:46,095
enough to say that we'll see this through.

1246
01:02:46,179 --> 01:02:48,514
And one day, it will just happen.

1247
01:02:48,598 --> 01:02:50,600
I think we all had one vision,

1248
01:02:50,683 --> 01:02:53,561
and that's to make these girls succeed.

1249
01:02:53,644 --> 01:02:56,397
From <i>Da Coconut Nut</i>
that was their pre-debut

1250
01:02:56,481 --> 01:02:58,483
in November 2021,

1251
01:02:58,566 --> 01:03:01,486
to a summer song in 2023,

1252
01:03:01,569 --> 01:03:03,654
it seemed like a full-circle.

1253
01:03:03,738 --> 01:03:05,364
And... ta-da!

1254
01:03:05,448 --> 01:03:12,121
["Pantropiko" playing]

1255
01:03:15,458 --> 01:03:22,423
["Pantropiko" playing]

1256
01:03:24,842 --> 01:03:26,385
I expected <i>Pantropiko</i> to make some noise,

1257
01:03:26,469 --> 01:03:30,181
but I never thought
it'd make BINI a household name.

1258
01:03:30,264 --> 01:03:32,141
That song started it all.

1259
01:03:32,225 --> 01:03:34,477
We finally found BINI's sound.

1260
01:03:34,560 --> 01:03:35,770
It's bubblegum pop.

1261
01:03:35,853 --> 01:03:42,568
["Pantropiko" continues]

1262
01:03:52,245 --> 01:03:53,246
[cheering]

1263
01:03:53,329 --> 01:03:56,582
We love you, BINI! [clapping]

1264
01:03:57,667 --> 01:03:59,794
Someone's tearing up!

1265
01:03:59,877 --> 01:04:02,213
It's my first time
to see Director Lauren dance.

1266
01:04:02,296 --> 01:04:04,006
- I know.
- Aww.

1267
01:04:04,090 --> 01:04:06,801
- Oh my god!
- I'm sweaty.

1268
01:04:06,884 --> 01:04:09,136
[Lauren] From where we started,

1269
01:04:09,220 --> 01:04:12,682
we didn't realize that 2024
would be the year for BINI.

1270
01:04:12,765 --> 01:04:19,480
[thrilling music playing]

1271
01:04:26,112 --> 01:04:30,700
[Colet] At the start of summer,
<i>Pantropiko</i> was already making waves.

1272
01:04:30,783 --> 01:04:34,495
We saw an increase
in their monthly listeners.

1273
01:04:34,579 --> 01:04:41,210
[thrilling music playing]

1274
01:04:41,294 --> 01:04:45,464
[cheering]

1275
01:04:45,548 --> 01:04:51,804
["Pantropiko" playing]

1276
01:05:00,396 --> 01:05:02,690
[Sheena] Initially,
I was very overwhelmed.

1277
01:05:02,773 --> 01:05:03,608
It said "DC (dance choreographer)

1278
01:05:03,691 --> 01:05:05,151
Sheena Catacutan."

1279
01:05:05,234 --> 01:05:06,319
It warmed my heart

1280
01:05:06,402 --> 01:05:08,404
that so many people
appreciated my choreography,

1281
01:05:08,487 --> 01:05:11,115
especially since it was my first time
choreographing for BINI.

1282
01:05:11,198 --> 01:05:14,827
It's true that when a song blows up,
people check out your whole discography.

1283
01:05:14,911 --> 01:05:17,246
<i>P-pop. This is Filipino?!</i>

1284
01:05:17,330 --> 01:05:18,581
<i>People of YouTube,</i>

1285
01:05:18,664 --> 01:05:20,499
<i>I don't know what I'm doing here!</i>

1286
01:05:20,583 --> 01:05:22,501
<i>And who is that?</i>

1287
01:05:22,585 --> 01:05:25,504
<i>Oh my gosh! Wait!</i>

1288
01:05:25,588 --> 01:05:28,716
<i>"I'm ready to be called
your princess. Hey!"</i>

1289
01:05:28,799 --> 01:05:31,093
All of a sudden, BINI is everywhere

1290
01:05:31,177 --> 01:05:32,929
and everybody wants BINI.

1291
01:05:33,012 --> 01:05:39,226
[cheering]

1292
01:05:39,310 --> 01:05:41,228
Inquiries came pouring in.

1293
01:05:41,312 --> 01:05:42,980
So many endorsements
and interested brands.

1294
01:05:43,064 --> 01:05:45,191
I thought it was just me
because I work with BINI,

1295
01:05:45,274 --> 01:05:48,569
but I noticed that everyone
was talking about BINI.

1296
01:05:48,653 --> 01:05:50,279
[audience cheering]

1297
01:05:50,363 --> 01:05:53,240
<i>- Ey!
- Ey!</i>

1298
01:05:53,324 --> 01:05:55,701
When people say, "Dress up like BINI,"

1299
01:05:55,785 --> 01:05:58,204
they know what you mean.

1300
01:05:59,163 --> 01:06:06,170
[cheering]

1301
01:06:06,796 --> 01:06:11,884
[Stacey] Our videos went viral,
like the BINI Core where we goof around.

1302
01:06:11,968 --> 01:06:14,387
People seem to really love
that side of us.

1303
01:06:14,804 --> 01:06:18,683
From the very beginning,
this is what we've envisioned for BINI.

1304
01:06:18,766 --> 01:06:20,184
They deserve all the success.

1305
01:06:20,267 --> 01:06:27,191
- [audience cheering]
- ["Karera" playing]

1306
01:06:27,274 --> 01:06:31,862
[Anna] The message of the song is spot-on.

1307
01:06:31,946 --> 01:06:37,868
It's what resonated the most
with the group and the team.

1308
01:06:37,952 --> 01:06:44,667
- [cheering]
- ["Karera" continues]

1309
01:07:01,225 --> 01:07:08,190
- ["Karera" continues]
- [audience cheering]

1310
01:07:27,376 --> 01:07:32,506
[pensive music playing]

1311
01:07:32,590 --> 01:07:34,508
[Colet] Maybe it's because
she's the big sister,

1312
01:07:34,592 --> 01:07:37,595
so she felt like
it'd be a burden to others

1313
01:07:37,678 --> 01:07:40,806
if she shared her worries with the group.

1314
01:07:40,890 --> 01:07:41,807
She kept them bottled up.

1315
01:07:41,891 --> 01:07:43,809
[Sheena] Actually,
she wasn't in a good place

1316
01:07:43,893 --> 01:07:45,603
throughout the entire concert preparation.

1317
01:07:45,686 --> 01:07:51,275
The best thing we could do
was not to pressure her into telling us.

1318
01:07:51,358 --> 01:07:55,237
If she's not in the mood to talk,
we understand.

1319
01:07:55,321 --> 01:07:58,532
We don't want to pressure her
to be okay right away.

1320
01:07:59,617 --> 01:08:03,454
I was actually thinking
if I should open this up,

1321
01:08:03,537 --> 01:08:05,289
because it's also a scary thing

1322
01:08:05,372 --> 01:08:09,293
to open your vulnerable self to everyone.

1323
01:08:09,376 --> 01:08:12,880
Because you never know
if it will be used against you.

1324
01:08:12,963 --> 01:08:15,007
But I thought about it.

1325
01:08:15,091 --> 01:08:18,719
Many people don't talk about these things.

1326
01:08:18,803 --> 01:08:21,347
But because of that,
they felt seen and heard.

1327
01:08:21,430 --> 01:08:25,184
If sharing my experience
can help someone, then I will.

1328
01:08:25,267 --> 01:08:26,894
[pensive music playing]

1329
01:08:26,977 --> 01:08:29,563
[Aiah] It all started on BINI Day.

1330
01:08:29,647 --> 01:08:31,482
I didn't see it coming.

1331
01:08:31,565 --> 01:08:34,610
I was super happy, having fun.

1332
01:08:34,693 --> 01:08:37,571
I was taking photos of everybody.

1333
01:08:38,572 --> 01:08:45,412
Then on our way home,
it was like a switch flipped.

1334
01:08:45,496 --> 01:08:49,834
[pensive music continues]

1335
01:08:49,917 --> 01:08:52,419
[Jhoanna] What happened
to Aiah was not new to us.

1336
01:08:52,503 --> 01:08:55,381
There'd been times before
when she had episodes,

1337
01:08:55,464 --> 01:08:57,842
but that was the worst one.

1338
01:08:57,925 --> 01:09:00,261
[cheering]

1339
01:09:00,344 --> 01:09:02,388
[Aiah] I was very pressured with school.

1340
01:09:02,471 --> 01:09:04,765
That time, we were stuck at home.

1341
01:09:04,849 --> 01:09:07,184
I didn't get to see my family,
my friends that much.

1342
01:09:07,268 --> 01:09:09,728
So I didn't have an outlet.

1343
01:09:09,812 --> 01:09:11,397
We were inside the elevator after BINI Day

1344
01:09:11,480 --> 01:09:12,815
when she got triggered.

1345
01:09:12,898 --> 01:09:15,776
I was holding her hand then.

1346
01:09:15,860 --> 01:09:19,280
It was scary because her grip got tighter.

1347
01:09:19,363 --> 01:09:21,949
It felt like she was losing control.

1348
01:09:22,032 --> 01:09:24,285
Aiah didn't overcome it overnight.

1349
01:09:24,368 --> 01:09:29,248
It was a struggle from that day
until the BINIverse concert.

1350
01:09:29,331 --> 01:09:32,585
The song I'm excited
to perform on BINIverse is...

1351
01:09:32,668 --> 01:09:34,587
[MQ] I started to get nervous.

1352
01:09:34,670 --> 01:09:37,715
First of all, I was worried
about the girls.

1353
01:09:37,798 --> 01:09:39,675
Could they pull it off?

1354
01:09:39,758 --> 01:09:43,929
Keep it light. One, two, three...

1355
01:09:46,390 --> 01:09:48,976
[Mikha] I was so worried.
I was so worried.

1356
01:09:49,059 --> 01:09:52,271
Actually, I felt bad for all of us

1357
01:09:52,354 --> 01:09:54,481
because our schedule was crazy.

1358
01:09:54,565 --> 01:09:58,319
[pensive music playing]

1359
01:09:58,402 --> 01:10:01,197
Hello! Hello, everyone.

1360
01:10:02,364 --> 01:10:05,409
Hi, girls. Congratulations.

1361
01:10:05,492 --> 01:10:08,704
[Mikha] I guess, for Aiah,
something triggered her.

1362
01:10:08,787 --> 01:10:10,706
She just couldn't stop it, you know?

1363
01:10:10,789 --> 01:10:12,583
Are you okay?

1364
01:10:12,666 --> 01:10:14,376
It's like I had an anxiety attack.

1365
01:10:14,460 --> 01:10:18,214
It was the first time in my life
that I couldn't look people in the eye.

1366
01:10:18,297 --> 01:10:22,009
Whenever I pulled off my mask,
I'd feel so naked. I'd feel so seen.

1367
01:10:22,092 --> 01:10:23,219
It was so uncomfortable.

1368
01:10:23,302 --> 01:10:25,512
That's why I'd wear a cap,
a mask, and a hoodie.

1369
01:10:25,596 --> 01:10:28,766
Of course, we offered
to get her professional help.

1370
01:10:28,849 --> 01:10:29,892
At least she was able to talk about it.

1371
01:10:29,975 --> 01:10:32,811
[cheering]

1372
01:10:32,895 --> 01:10:34,939
[Matthew] I stayed with her
for, like, a week.

1373
01:10:35,022 --> 01:10:36,857
I was the one who looked after her.

1374
01:10:36,941 --> 01:10:38,567
My mom came to the rescue.

1375
01:10:38,651 --> 01:10:42,696
Just having her there made me feel better.

1376
01:10:42,780 --> 01:10:46,909
Even if you say, "Aiah, I'm here
if you need someone to talk to,"

1377
01:10:46,992 --> 01:10:48,702
it's still up to her.

1378
01:10:48,786 --> 01:10:50,412
This is yours, Colet.

1379
01:10:50,496 --> 01:10:54,917
[Maan] You see, these girls
always say they can do it.

1380
01:10:55,000 --> 01:10:59,088
No matter how they're feeling,
they will always say yes.

1381
01:11:05,594 --> 01:11:07,596
[Maan] During rehearsals,

1382
01:11:07,680 --> 01:11:10,766
I kept asking Aiah if she could do it.

1383
01:11:10,849 --> 01:11:12,768
When she said she wasn't sure...

1384
01:11:12,851 --> 01:11:15,813
- [cheering]
- ...that's when I started to worry.

1385
01:11:18,816 --> 01:11:20,359
Everyone is there. It's all full.

1386
01:11:20,442 --> 01:11:22,820
So we started the countdown. This is it.

1387
01:11:22,903 --> 01:11:25,197
From the chromic BINIverse,
it will be colorful.

1388
01:11:25,281 --> 01:11:31,495
- [tense music playing]
- [cheering]

1389
01:11:35,207 --> 01:11:38,585
We are on the cusp. And, uh...

1390
01:11:39,795 --> 01:11:42,214
I don't want to add any more pressure.

1391
01:11:42,298 --> 01:11:44,091
- Enjoy the concert!
- Enjoy, girls!

1392
01:11:44,174 --> 01:11:48,178
[cheering, clapping]

1393
01:11:48,262 --> 01:11:51,598
A couple of minutes before it started,

1394
01:11:51,682 --> 01:11:53,892
I caught a glimpse of the audience.

1395
01:11:53,976 --> 01:11:58,272
[cheering]

1396
01:11:58,355 --> 01:12:01,191
- Go, BINI!
- Go, girls! Let's do it!

1397
01:12:01,275 --> 01:12:04,403
[cheering, clapping]

1398
01:12:04,486 --> 01:12:07,614
[tense music playing] [cheering]

1399
01:12:07,698 --> 01:12:11,785
- Let's go, Aiah!
- Let's go, Aiah!

1400
01:12:12,786 --> 01:12:15,581
[Colet] We weren't sure
if she'd be able to perform,

1401
01:12:15,664 --> 01:12:19,168
or if we would be complete
for our first concert.

1402
01:12:20,085 --> 01:12:23,213
[Sheena] My energy was probably at 143%.

1403
01:12:23,297 --> 01:12:25,382
So I shared the 43% with the girls.

1404
01:12:25,466 --> 01:12:28,886
- [tense music playing]
- [audience cheering]

1405
01:12:28,969 --> 01:12:30,804
Oh my gosh! So many people!

1406
01:12:30,888 --> 01:12:33,307
No, no! Breathe!

1407
01:12:33,390 --> 01:12:36,977
Breathe! Just keep breathing!

1408
01:12:37,895 --> 01:12:40,147
- You can do this!
- Breathe!

1409
01:12:42,066 --> 01:12:43,484
You got this, Aiah. We're right here.

1410
01:12:43,567 --> 01:12:44,693
Oh my god!

1411
01:12:44,777 --> 01:12:46,403
[audience cheering]

1412
01:12:46,487 --> 01:12:50,908
- Smile! Smile!
- Smile! Breathe! You got this!

1413
01:12:50,991 --> 01:12:53,786
You got this! We're right here.

1414
01:12:53,869 --> 01:12:55,204
Whoo!

1415
01:12:55,287 --> 01:12:56,914
Let's go! Let's go!

1416
01:12:56,997 --> 01:12:59,208
Hold her steady. Go, go, go!

1417
01:12:59,291 --> 01:13:00,417
You got this!

1418
01:13:00,501 --> 01:13:04,213
[audience cheering]

1419
01:13:04,296 --> 01:13:06,799
We can do this! Inhale, exhale.

1420
01:13:06,882 --> 01:13:09,802
Don't think about it.
Imagine they're not there.

1421
01:13:11,095 --> 01:13:12,888
Imagine we're just in Makati.

1422
01:13:12,971 --> 01:13:15,599
You can do it! We got this!

1423
01:13:17,684 --> 01:13:21,021
I was still trying to gauge
at that time if I could do it.

1424
01:13:21,105 --> 01:13:24,108
I wasn't 100% sure
if I could interact with

1425
01:13:24,191 --> 01:13:27,069
or even look at the audience.

1426
01:13:27,152 --> 01:13:30,989
Aiah was really trying
to power through it.

1427
01:13:31,073 --> 01:13:33,617
But she had a hard time
controlling her emotions.

1428
01:13:33,700 --> 01:13:36,870
We made her feel that
all her feelings were valid.

1429
01:13:36,954 --> 01:13:38,956
There are just some things
that are beyond our control.

1430
01:13:40,999 --> 01:13:42,167
You can do it.

1431
01:13:43,377 --> 01:13:47,339
This year, we've been
really put to the test.

1432
01:13:47,423 --> 01:13:50,509
- It's our first concert day.
- Let's have fun, okay?

1433
01:13:50,592 --> 01:13:51,510
[Sheena] It was just us back then.

1434
01:13:51,593 --> 01:13:53,804
So, we're the only ones who really know

1435
01:13:53,887 --> 01:13:55,973
what we've all been through.

1436
01:13:56,056 --> 01:14:01,854
[Mikha] I'm very grateful to them
for the profound happiness they bring me.

1437
01:14:01,937 --> 01:14:03,439
What we went through was really tough.

1438
01:14:03,522 --> 01:14:06,984
It could have been so easy
to step out and quit.

1439
01:14:07,067 --> 01:14:10,070
[Reden] I was really hoping that
when they get revealed on stage,

1440
01:14:10,154 --> 01:14:13,073
Aiah would feel how much
so many people love her.

1441
01:14:13,157 --> 01:14:14,992
We don't know when
we'll have this chance again.

1442
01:14:15,075 --> 01:14:16,702
It will be a fun
yet exhausting experience.

1443
01:14:16,785 --> 01:14:18,871
But this is something
we won't want to miss.

1444
01:14:20,080 --> 01:14:22,082
- Yeah!
- Game!

1445
01:14:22,166 --> 01:14:23,000
Five, six, seven... go!

1446
01:14:23,083 --> 01:14:26,086
- B. I. N. I.
- B. I. N. I.

1447
01:14:26,170 --> 01:14:27,463
BINI!

1448
01:14:27,546 --> 01:14:32,217
BINIverse!

1449
01:14:34,094 --> 01:14:40,684
[audience cheering]

1450
01:14:48,400 --> 01:14:54,990
[singing "Na Na Na"]

1451
01:15:03,290 --> 01:15:04,500
[Aiah] Every time I would feel anxious,

1452
01:15:04,583 --> 01:15:06,960
I would just look
at my family and friends.

1453
01:15:07,044 --> 01:15:11,840
My friends made signs for me to look at
in case I felt jittery on stage.

1454
01:15:13,717 --> 01:15:19,890
But when Aiah flashed her signature smile,
I said, "We're good. Aiah's okay now."

1455
01:15:19,973 --> 01:15:23,644
I was like, "Oh my god! This is it.
We will have a great show!"

1456
01:15:23,727 --> 01:15:30,067
[continues singing "Na Na Na"]

1457
01:15:30,943 --> 01:15:36,365
I really felt it,
and I chose to feel all of it.

1458
01:15:36,448 --> 01:15:40,494
So after feeling all of it
and going through it,

1459
01:15:40,577 --> 01:15:42,621
I get to learn how to move forward.

1460
01:15:42,704 --> 01:15:47,376
[continues singing "Na Na Na"]

1461
01:15:47,459 --> 01:15:48,585
Thank you, Lord!

1462
01:15:48,669 --> 01:15:51,088
[audience cheering]

1463
01:15:51,171 --> 01:15:53,465
Oh my god! I survived!

1464
01:15:53,549 --> 01:15:58,345
I just hope that we continue
to make everyone feel safe.

1465
01:15:58,428 --> 01:16:02,766
[suspenseful music playing]

1466
01:16:02,849 --> 01:16:05,227
One concert is hard enough.

1467
01:16:05,310 --> 01:16:07,437
Can they survive three days?

1468
01:16:07,521 --> 01:16:10,399
[Gwen] I knew something was up.
I wasn't feeling very well.

1469
01:16:10,482 --> 01:16:12,276
It was like radiating to my nostrils.

1470
01:16:12,359 --> 01:16:15,529
There was this heavy feeling
stuck in my throat.

1471
01:16:17,155 --> 01:16:19,741
["Woman Like me" instrumental playing]

1472
01:16:19,825 --> 01:16:22,995
Guys, Gwen lost her voice today.

1473
01:16:23,078 --> 01:16:25,289
But look at her go!

1474
01:16:25,372 --> 01:16:26,915
[Lauren] I didn't sense it.

1475
01:16:26,999 --> 01:16:28,458
But I knew Gwen was under the weather.

1476
01:16:28,542 --> 01:16:32,588
No one noticed because
Gwen didn't let it show.

1477
01:16:32,671 --> 01:16:34,673
[audience chanting]

1478
01:16:34,756 --> 01:16:36,258
[Gwen] Every time I exited the stage,

1479
01:16:36,341 --> 01:16:37,801
I felt like I was running out of air.

1480
01:16:37,884 --> 01:16:41,597
I remember blacking out for a bit.

1481
01:16:41,680 --> 01:16:45,392
- [audience cheering]
- [indistinct chatter]

1482
01:16:45,475 --> 01:16:46,893
Can she power through?

1483
01:16:46,977 --> 01:16:49,771
What are we going to tell people?

1484
01:16:49,855 --> 01:16:53,358
I was like, "Hold on, I'm back.
I need to get up now."

1485
01:16:53,442 --> 01:16:56,820
[Jovy] Actually, we were worried
she might collapse on stage.

1486
01:16:56,903 --> 01:16:59,114
So, we were constantly on the
lookout every time she exited,

1487
01:16:59,197 --> 01:17:02,909
checking her blood pressure
and oxygen levels.

1488
01:17:02,993 --> 01:17:05,787
She just needs to get through
<i>Pantropiko</i> and the finale.

1489
01:17:05,871 --> 01:17:07,873
- She's about to collapse.
- If she can't go on anymore,

1490
01:17:07,956 --> 01:17:09,583
the other girls would step in.

1491
01:17:09,666 --> 01:17:11,793
[Lauren] The ambulance was on standby

1492
01:17:11,877 --> 01:17:14,463
in case she needed
to be rushed to the hospital.

1493
01:17:14,546 --> 01:17:18,383
But Gwen herself refused to go.

1494
01:17:18,467 --> 01:17:19,801
She only asked for time to recover.

1495
01:17:19,885 --> 01:17:22,262
I was amazed by her will to do this.

1496
01:17:22,346 --> 01:17:26,058
That slender young woman
was really determined!

1497
01:17:26,141 --> 01:17:27,768
She did it, and she performed.

1498
01:17:27,851 --> 01:17:32,064
[audience chanting]
BINI! BINI! BINI! BINI!

1499
01:17:37,778 --> 01:17:39,488
[Stacey] Gwen didn't want
to sit this one out,

1500
01:17:39,571 --> 01:17:45,577
so she really powered through the fatigue,
the stress, the heat...

1501
01:17:45,661 --> 01:17:48,622
I was shocked when I looked over at Gwen
because her nose was bleeding.

1502
01:17:48,705 --> 01:17:50,082
Apply a cold compress.

1503
01:17:56,171 --> 01:17:58,465
[Sheena] Gwen finished the show

1504
01:17:58,548 --> 01:17:59,883
because she didn't want us
to be inconvenienced

1505
01:17:59,966 --> 01:18:02,177
by the possible changes.

1506
01:18:02,260 --> 01:18:06,473
You see, we have that tendency to show up,
even when we're not feeling our best,

1507
01:18:06,556 --> 01:18:08,558
because we don't want the
other girls to have to adjust.

1508
01:18:09,267 --> 01:18:11,478
[Jhoanna] Gwen's really fragile.

1509
01:18:11,561 --> 01:18:13,689
If only I could... Tsk. Jeez!

1510
01:18:13,772 --> 01:18:16,400
- [somber music playing]
- [sniffles]

1511
01:18:16,483 --> 01:18:18,568
[sobs softly]

1512
01:18:18,652 --> 01:18:22,698
If only I could take that pain
away from her, I would.

1513
01:18:23,073 --> 01:18:29,871
I think one of my good traits is
not getting disheartened easily.

1514
01:18:29,955 --> 01:18:31,665
So, I'd gladly trade places with Gwen.

1515
01:18:31,748 --> 01:18:32,999
The Blooms waited so long for it.

1516
01:18:33,083 --> 01:18:36,128
They deserve to see a great show.

1517
01:18:36,211 --> 01:18:39,423
That's what was running through my head.
They deserve to see us rock it.

1518
01:18:39,506 --> 01:18:41,466
There's dirt on their hands. [laughs]

1519
01:18:41,550 --> 01:18:42,676
- Let's go!
- Alright.

1520
01:18:42,759 --> 01:18:44,136
[shrieks]

1521
01:18:44,219 --> 01:18:46,096
[indistinct chatter]

1522
01:18:46,179 --> 01:18:48,014
[MQ] That's when it hit me.

1523
01:18:48,098 --> 01:18:51,768
Oh my god!
There's no stopping these girls.

1524
01:18:51,852 --> 01:18:54,396
They're serious about fighting
for their dreams.

1525
01:18:54,479 --> 01:18:57,399
Last day! Last day! [clapping]

1526
01:18:57,482 --> 01:18:59,276
Whoo!

1527
01:18:59,359 --> 01:19:00,986
We all feel the same way

1528
01:19:01,069 --> 01:19:02,779
because we're together on this journey.

1529
01:19:02,863 --> 01:19:05,157
[Lauren] They've gone a long way.

1530
01:19:06,283 --> 01:19:08,618
They deserve to be on that stage.

1531
01:19:08,702 --> 01:19:14,624
[thrilling music playing]

1532
01:19:26,553 --> 01:19:29,598
These girls want to give their best.

1533
01:19:29,681 --> 01:19:32,434
They want to give their best
to their fans.

1534
01:19:33,477 --> 01:19:35,520
[Ica] I pray for their protection.

1535
01:19:35,604 --> 01:19:38,315
I pray that people protect them
and understand them better

1536
01:19:38,398 --> 01:19:40,901
because, at the end of the day,
they're still kids

1537
01:19:40,984 --> 01:19:45,405
who need protection and
guidance from their elders.

1538
01:19:45,489 --> 01:19:47,073
[Reden] They deserve it.

1539
01:19:47,157 --> 01:19:52,954
These girls have been through so much.

1540
01:19:53,038 --> 01:19:55,707
But it all makes sense now.

1541
01:19:55,791 --> 01:20:01,338
The struggles and disagreements they had
prepared them for this.

1542
01:20:01,421 --> 01:20:04,716
[thrilling music continues]

1543
01:20:04,800 --> 01:20:06,384
[Anna] There's really something
special about them.

1544
01:20:06,468 --> 01:20:08,595
It's not just how they sing,
but also their personalities.

1545
01:20:08,678 --> 01:20:12,182
Each one of them has
something unique to offer.

1546
01:20:12,265 --> 01:20:18,772
[audience chanting]
BINI! BINI! BINI! BINI!

1547
01:20:19,397 --> 01:20:22,609
[Aiah] It's about all of us girls
and the people who believe in us.

1548
01:20:22,692 --> 01:20:25,070
The place was filled
with love and support.

1549
01:20:25,153 --> 01:20:27,239
At the end of the day, love prevailed.

1550
01:20:27,322 --> 01:20:29,241
It felt like a safe space for me.

1551
01:20:33,119 --> 01:20:35,413
[Jhoanna] Whatever the reason
for me to give up,

1552
01:20:35,497 --> 01:20:40,544
they will always be enough
reason for me to stay.

1553
01:20:40,627 --> 01:20:46,675
[dramatic music playing]

1554
01:20:52,055 --> 01:20:58,687
[singing "Born To Win"]

1555
01:21:06,486 --> 01:21:08,905
[Mikha] I think she was
the right choice for our leader.

1556
01:21:08,989 --> 01:21:12,492
I'm very proud of her because
she stays strong for all of us.

1557
01:21:12,576 --> 01:21:13,493
- We're ready.
- Are you ready?

1558
01:21:13,577 --> 01:21:14,703
Let's go, girls.

1559
01:21:14,786 --> 01:21:18,081
[Aiah] I know, as a leader,
she's had it rough many times,

1560
01:21:18,164 --> 01:21:20,542
but she handles it very well.

1561
01:21:20,625 --> 01:21:22,794
We all depend on Jho.
We go with whatever she decides.

1562
01:21:22,878 --> 01:21:25,964
Even though we're older than her,
we follow her.

1563
01:21:26,047 --> 01:21:32,220
[continues singing "Born To Win"]

1564
01:21:33,597 --> 01:21:39,227
[audience cheering]

1565
01:21:39,311 --> 01:21:40,604
[Jhoanna] Among us eight,
Colet was the one

1566
01:21:40,687 --> 01:21:42,981
who had to change her ways the most.

1567
01:21:43,064 --> 01:21:44,858
She's always looking out
for the rest of us seven.

1568
01:21:44,941 --> 01:21:46,192
[continues singing "Born To Win"]

1569
01:21:46,276 --> 01:21:48,361
[Sheena] More than a sister,
she's like a mother to us.

1570
01:21:48,445 --> 01:21:50,739
She mothered so hard. [laughing]

1571
01:21:50,822 --> 01:21:53,199
[continues singing "Born To Win"]

1572
01:21:53,283 --> 01:21:56,077
[Maloi] My dad worked overseas
for thirteen years.

1573
01:21:56,161 --> 01:21:59,080
He came home for good
three years ago to be with us.

1574
01:21:59,164 --> 01:22:02,792
<i>I have to go. Bye!</i>

1575
01:22:03,752 --> 01:22:07,088
<i>I'm not sure when I'll be back.</i>

1576
01:22:07,172 --> 01:22:09,966
I miss them all the time. [sobs softly]

1577
01:22:11,468 --> 01:22:15,096
[continues singing "Born To Win"]

1578
01:22:15,180 --> 01:22:18,600
It was actually my mom
who convinced me to audition.

1579
01:22:18,683 --> 01:22:22,520
She's the OG fashionista.
She's my role model.

1580
01:22:24,689 --> 01:22:26,816
[Gwen] Stacey's always been like that.

1581
01:22:26,900 --> 01:22:29,486
Maybe, at first,
she didn't show you her playful side,

1582
01:22:29,569 --> 01:22:31,112
but she's always been pretty hyper.

1583
01:22:31,196 --> 01:22:36,701
[continues singing "Born To Win"]

1584
01:22:36,785 --> 01:22:39,079
[Mikha] They don't really
get to watch me a lot

1585
01:22:39,162 --> 01:22:41,456
because we live separately.

1586
01:22:41,539 --> 01:22:44,501
When I experienced them watching me...

1587
01:22:51,091 --> 01:22:55,428
Mikha puts on this tough act,
but deep down, she's a crybaby. [chuckles]

1588
01:22:55,512 --> 01:22:58,473
It's unfair. Just kidding! [chuckles]

1589
01:23:03,770 --> 01:23:04,771
[Sheena] Oh my gosh!

1590
01:23:04,854 --> 01:23:08,566
My grandma, my brother, and Baket
watched me for the first time ever!

1591
01:23:08,650 --> 01:23:11,194
Baket was my nanny when I was a baby.

1592
01:23:11,277 --> 01:23:13,279
I fought back tears the entire concert.

1593
01:23:13,363 --> 01:23:16,408
[Sheena] My grandma watched me
perform tonight.

1594
01:23:16,491 --> 01:23:19,077
Grandma, please wave.

1595
01:23:22,747 --> 01:23:27,293
My baby is the softest,
sweetest human being.

1596
01:23:27,377 --> 01:23:28,878
I'm super clingy to Gwen.

1597
01:23:28,962 --> 01:23:31,965
I could never be that clingy to Jho.

1598
01:23:32,048 --> 01:23:33,633
I'd be so grossed out.

1599
01:23:36,511 --> 01:23:38,805
[Mikha] I think Aiah is doing better now.

1600
01:23:38,888 --> 01:23:42,809
And I hope that she realizes
that she's not alone in this.

1601
01:23:43,852 --> 01:23:47,188
[audience cheering]

1602
01:23:49,274 --> 01:23:51,776
Whoo!

1603
01:23:51,860 --> 01:23:53,528
We're ready for Araneta!

1604
01:23:55,071 --> 01:23:55,905
[shrieking]

1605
01:23:55,989 --> 01:24:00,118
Congrats! Whoo! [clapping]

1606
01:24:00,201 --> 01:24:07,083
["8" playing]

1607
01:24:10,503 --> 01:24:12,213
One, two, three...

1608
01:24:12,297 --> 01:24:15,216
Yes! We can finally get some sleep!

1609
01:24:20,722 --> 01:24:24,100
[Gwen] This is the year
everything changed for us.

1610
01:24:24,184 --> 01:24:27,812
And so, our bond really grew stronger.

1611
01:24:27,896 --> 01:24:29,064
Get some rest.

1612
01:24:29,147 --> 01:24:31,608
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1613
01:24:31,691 --> 01:24:32,817
[Sheena] Of course, my dream for BINI

1614
01:24:32,901 --> 01:24:35,987
is for us to keep this success going.

1615
01:24:36,071 --> 01:24:40,575
We're scared it will just
be a flash in the pan.

1616
01:24:40,658 --> 01:24:44,079
We really hope to become
an international girl group.

1617
01:24:44,162 --> 01:24:46,790
Not just here in the Philippines
but all over the world.

1618
01:24:47,999 --> 01:24:52,170
[Jhoanna] I really think it was
meant for the eight of us

1619
01:24:52,253 --> 01:24:53,797
to be part of BINI.

1620
01:24:53,880 --> 01:24:55,799
It was really destined.

1621
01:24:55,882 --> 01:24:57,383
Five, six, seven... go!

1622
01:24:57,467 --> 01:24:59,803
- B. I. N. I.
- B. I. N. I.

1623
01:24:59,886 --> 01:25:01,513
BINI!

1624
01:25:01,596 --> 01:25:04,224
Eight until the end!

1625
01:25:04,307 --> 01:25:05,308
Whoo!

1626
01:25:05,391 --> 01:25:12,273
["8" continues]

1627
01:25:38,800 --> 01:25:45,682
["8" continues]

1628
01:26:26,598 --> 01:26:33,479
["8" continues]

1629
01:27:03,885 --> 01:27:10,767
["8" continues]

1630
01:27:46,636 --> 01:27:53,518
["8" continues]

1631
01:28:05,989 --> 01:28:08,199
[laughing]

1632
01:28:08,283 --> 01:28:10,034
<i>Oh my god!</i>
